<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="2CO" stage="Final" version="C">
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">2 Korintus</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Sasuri Paulus ka dua<bt>Paul's second letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">hia dhèu parcaya ètu kota Korintus<bt>to the *believers in the city of Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">2 Korintus<bt>2 Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii Maho'o<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Sasuri ne nèti ja'a, Paulus. Ama Lamatua pua-paleha ja'a sèna ka laku lole lula-nèti Yesus Kristus dènge dhèu asa mia-mia. Yesus Kristus èèna, dhu Ama Lamatua paj'uj'u karèi nèti uru-uru ka. Ari èdhi Timotius ètu ne'e kahèi. Na hia lii maho'o.<bt>This letter is from me, Paulus. God has sent/commissioned (doublet) me to go tell/explain about Yesus Kristus to people everywhere. That Yesus Kristus is the one whom God designated beforehand from long ago. Our-inc younger sibling Timotius is also here. He sends greetings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ja'a pa'adhu sasuri ne'e mi dhèu parcaya aa'i-aa'i dhu biasa pakaboko ètu kota Korintus dènge propensi Akaya.<bt>I write this letter to all believers who normally/customarily gather in the city of Korintus and the province of Akaya.</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 18:1</note><v n="2" />Ja'a sabaj'a mi Ama èdhi, nuka Ama Lamatua, dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Ja'a manèngi ho Rèngu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Ra dènge miu, sèna ka miu mamuri dame dènge mera-milu.<bt>I pray2 to God, that is our-inc Father, and our Head Yesus Kristus. I request that They show Their goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-pl, so that you can live at peace (relationships), and safe (external peace). [EXEG: 2 of 3 senses of peace; commentaries that want to restrict it to just inner peace haven't done their homework.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua<bt>Paulus gives thanks to God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dad'èi ji'i ka ladhe dhèu aa'i-aa'i ded'e padedha-dedha kolongara Ama Lamatua. Te Nèngu èèna, Ama nèti Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Rasa kasia aa'i-aa'i kapua nèti Nèngu, aa Nèngu ka dhu pa'èra d'ara èdhi.<bt>We-exc want/desire for everyone to elevate on high/exalt the name/reputation of God. Cuz (elaboration) He is the Father of our-inc Head Yesus Kristus. All sense of mercy/pity is rooted/sourced in Him, and He is the one who strengthens/encourages our-inc insides. [NLT]</bt><v n="4" />Nèngu ka pamaho'o d'ara èdhi ladhe èdhi ètu d'ara sasusa. Nèti èèna ka, èdhi kahèi bisa pamaho'o dhèu leo dhu paraga dènge sasusa. Te èdhi bisa pa'èra d'ara rèngu, sama sèmi Lamatua pa'èra le d'ara èdhi.<bt>He is the one who comforts us when we encounter/experience trouble/difficulty/strife. That is why we are also able to comfort other people who encounter/experience trouble/difficulty/strife. Cuz (elaboration) we are able to strengthen/encourage their insides, just like God2 has strengthened/encouraged our insides.</bt><v n="5" />Kristus abhu le susa ae-ae hia èdhi. De, lula Kristus rasa le susa sèmi èèna, nèti èèna ka Ama Na pa'èra d'ara èdhi taruu, ladhe èdhi paraga dènge susa.<bt>Kristus has also got/experienced a lot of trouble/difficulty/strife for us/on our behalf. So (consequently), because Kristus has felt/experienced difficulty like that, that is why His Father keeps strengthening/encouraging our insides, if/when we get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife.</bt><v n="6" />Ladhe ji'i ètu ne'e abhu susa, Ama Lamatua pa'èra d'ara ji'i. Aa ladhe ji'i paraga dènge j'aj'èra, hèia taha dènge d'ara taleo, na, miu hud'i me'a kahèi, Lamatua pake j'ara sèmi ne'e sèna ka pa'èra d'ara miu, ho patalale miu nèti koasa bhabhelu-katub'a. Te ladhe miu abhu sasusa sama sèmi ji'i, Lamatua pa'èra d'ara miu, sèna ka miu bisa taha mere dènge d'ara taleo kahèi.<bt>If/when we-exc here get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife, God strengthens/encourages our-exc insides. And if/when we get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife2, and/then endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: wide insides), na, you-pl must also understand that God2 also uses that way/means to strengthen/encourage your-pl insides, to release/save2/spare you from evil (doublet). Cuz (elaboration) if/when you get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife like us-exc, God2 strengthens/encourage your insides, so that you are also able to endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: wide insides). [HCE] [EXEG: we-exc = ??; in 1:1 mentions Timothy, but later also mentions Silas, may be others; considerable commentary discussion about “epistilary ‘we’”. Implied proposition in first part (resonating with second part): “and/then endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: insides).” UNS's got stuck without it.]</bt><v n="7" />Nèti èèna ka, ji'i nge'a mèu, na, miu bisa taha mere dènge èra. Te ji'i nge'a, na, ladhe miu abhu j'aj'èra sama sèmi ji'i, Lamatua pa'èra d'ara miu, aa Nèngu pa'èra d'ara ji'i kahèi.<bt>That is why we are sure/confident that you-pl can endure strongly/firmly. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc know that if/when you get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife like us, God2 also strengthens/encourages your insides, and He also strengthens/encourages our insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalau-karèto"><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-03 02:21:12Z" status="Anyone">UNS not know</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Dad'èi ji'i sèna ka miu me'a mèu sasusa dhu ji'i abhu ètu propensi Asia. Ji'i rasa bia, risi nèti dhu ji'i bisa pasae, toke ji'i oe ele ngangee, lula ji'i pangee, na, ji'i madhe kèna.<bt>Siblings! Our-exc desire is for you-pl to really understand about that trouble/difficulty which we once experienced in the province of Asia. We felt heavy (sad, depressed), more than we were able to shoulder carry, to the point that we were about to give up/despair/lose hope, because we thought that we were about to die.</bt><note reference="1:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 15:32</note><v n="9" />Ji'i rasa bia, nuka sèmi dhèu èci ropa tadèngi hakim pama'ète hahuku pamadhe ne. Te ngaa aa'i-aa'i se j'aj'i, sèna ka ji'i parcaya Ama Lamatua, aa baku parcaya ngi'u ji'i unu mi. Te Lamatua èèna ka dhu unu koasa ho pamamuri hari dhèu madhe.<bt>We felt heavy (sad, depressed), like a person who has just heard the judge decide the death penalty for him. But all that happened, so that we-exc believed/trusted in God, and did not believe in ourselves. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who has the power/authority to bring dead people back to life.</bt><v n="10" />Nèngu ka dhu pakaj'èu <span class="Italic">le </span>ji'i nèti bhabhelu, lod'o ji'i oe madhe. Bèli-camèd'a Nèngu <span class="Italic">neo </span>pakaj'èu ji'i nèti bhabhelu-katub'a kahèi. Aa ji'i ma'ète boe sanao, sèna ka Na pakaj'èu <span class="Italic">taruu </span>ji'i nèti bhabhelu-katub'a.<bt>He is the one who <span class="Italic">has</span> freed/rescued/separated/saved us from evil when we were nearly dead. Later He also <span class="Italic">will</span> free/save us from evil (doublet). We continue to hope that He will later free/save us free evil things <span class="Italic">continually</span>.</bt><v n="11" />Ladhe miu loe boe sabaj'a hia ji'i, èèna ka soru-bara ji'i kahèi, te Ama Lamatua neo tao j'ara dhu be'a ae-ae hia mi ji'i. Nèngu tao j'ara èèna, lula dhèu ae dhu sabaj'a hia ji'i. Hèia lod'o dhèu ae sanèd'e ji'i, rèngu manèngi makasi ae-ae mi Ama Lamatua kahèi.<bt>If/when you donot stop praying for us-exc, that also helps (doublet) us, cuz (elaboration) God is going to do many good things for us-exc. He does that, because many people are praying for us-exc. So, when many people remember/think of us, they will also give many thanks to God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus nelu tao dhu hiu<bt>Paulus intends to do something new</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ji'i bisa koa-kad'iri iisi ji'i, lula ji'i nge'a ètu d'ara iiki ji'i, ngaa dhu ji'i ad'u-ue ètu rai-haha ne, madhutu dad'èi Lamatua dhu Na pangèd'u mi ji'i. Ji'i rai boe nèti sasab'a-la'a ne, sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa rèdhi ji'i sab'a dènge d'ara mola. Ji'i pakako sasab'a ji'i, pake boe mamèu<bt>We-exc could boast/brag (doublet), because we know in our small insides (=conscience) what it is that we do (doublet) in this world, is according to God2's will for us. We do not retreat/flee from that work/responsibility, so that everyone can see we are working with straight/just/honest insides (character &amp; motives). We carry out our work, not using the smarts/cleverness/wisdom</bt><note reference="1:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">A'abhu Paulus ètu ne'e, nuka &lt;mamèu dhu tao dhèu ngangee madhera, do re'a j'ara-j'ara madhutu ngangee Lamatua&gt;. Dènge sèmi èèna &lt;mamèu&gt; ne, mesa boe nèti kahadhu di, te ngaa nèti d'ara kahèi.<bt>Paulus' intention here is ‘smarts/cleverness/wisdom that makes a person think long (through things), or understand things according to God2's view’. In this way, this &lt;smarts/cleverness/wisdom&gt;, is not just from the brain/mind, but also from the insides (seat of emotions and character).</bt></note>dhu mai nèti rai-haha ne, te ngaa mamèu dhu kapua na nèti Ama Lamatua. Te Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ji'i. Nèti èèna ka, ji'i bisa asa tabha èra ètu d'ara sasab'a-la'a lod'o ji'i bera-bera dènge miu.<bt>which comes from this world, but using the smarts/cleverness/wisdom that is rooted/source in God. Cuz (elaboration) God2 shows His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity to us. That is why we are able to work increasingly stronger/harder while we were together with you. [HCE]</bt><v n="13" />Ja'a suri hia miu dhodhoka j'ara-j'ara dhu miu bisa baca aa bisa me'a mèu. Limuri ne miu me'a le naneo ja'a cahag'e. Te ngaa ja'a sanao, sèna ka bèli-camèd'a miu bisa me'a mèu risi hari.<bt>I write to you-pl only about matters/issues that you can read and understand. Now you already understand some/part of my purpose. But I hope later you will be able to understand even more completely/fully.</bt><v n="14" />Ne'e ne, miu me'a ciki era lula-nèti ji'i se. Te ngaa èèna na, lod'o Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus mai hari ka, ja'a ke'a, na, miu me'a j'ara ae-ae. Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu bisa koa-kad'iri ji'i, sama sèmi ji'i koa-kad'iri miu kahèi.<bt>Now, you-pl understand a little about us-exc. But later, when our-inc Head Yesus Kristus comes back, na, I know that you will understand a lot. In that way, you will be able to boast (doublet) about us-exc, just like we also boast about you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Lula ja'a ke'a, na, miu me'a j'ara aa'i-aa'i se, nèti èèna ka ca hari na, ja'a pama'ète kore le, ho dhiu ngad'o hari miu, sèna ka miu bisa abhu mèngi-nale dua hari.<bt>Because I know/trust that you-pl understand all these things, that is why previously, I had once decided to go see/check up on you again, so that you could get a blessing two times. [NOTE to daughter translations: avoid ambiguity: two times (volume of blessing) vs. two times (times seeing you)--the latter is what is intended here. Ex. Summ.]</bt><v n="16" />De uru èèna ja'a dhu pangee, ladhe j'aj'i laku asa propensi Makedonia, na, ja'a bisa dhuli ngad'o miu. Ho ladhe ja'a lèpa nèti Makedonia, ja'a bisa dhuli hari pa'asu-pareo dènge miu. Dènge sèmi èèna, miu bisa soru-bara ja'a, ho bisa laku taruu asa propensi Yudea.<bt>So (consequently), previously I was thinking if it worked out for me to go to the province of Makedonia, na, I could stop in and see you. So that when I came back from Makedonia, I could stop in and visit (doublet) you again. In that way, you could help (doublet) me, so I could continue travelling on to the province of Yudea. [EXEG: Scholars say 2 Cor was written from Macedonia, so this verse doesn't fit that, unless he is referring to a plan at an earlier time that was later changed. The key is the Gk /proteron/ in vs.15, which indicates “my earlier plan, I had been planning...but”.]</bt><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 19:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Te ngaa tasamia? Lod'o-lod'o ja'a peka, neo dhiu pangad'o dènge miu, ele boe mi pangee, na, ja'a uri kore mèka, si? Do, miu pangee, na, ja'a dhodhoka pama'ète madhutu dad'èi d'ara ja'a di, sama sèmi dhèu leo ètu rai-haha ne, si? Do, miu pangee, na, ja'a ne dhèu dhu peka leo, tao leo, ho d'èi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Oo.&gt;&gt; Aa te ngaa ja'a ngee ètu d'ara ja'a, na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o!&gt;&gt; Ele boe miu pangee, na, ja'a sèmi èèna ka, si?<bt>But how about it? Each time I tell (you) that I desire to come see you, perhaps/probably you-pl think/assume I keep delaying, or (what)? Or, you think/assume that I only decide things according to my own desires/wishes, like other people in this world, or (what)? Or, you think/assume I am a person who says one thing and does another, who likes to say, “Oo. (=yes, affirmation)” Whereas in fact in my insides, I am thinking, “No!” Perhaps/probably you are thinking that I am like that, 'right?</bt><v n="18" />Èdhi bisa parcaya Ama Lamatua, lula Nèngu peka ca j'ara, tatu Na tao madhutu. Nèti èèna ka, ji'i sama sèmi èèna kahèi. Ladhe ji'i dhaa, peka na, &lt;&lt;Oo,&gt;&gt; na ji'i pangee boe, na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc can believe/trust God, because He says something, surely He will do accordingly. That is why we-exc are also like that. If/when we speak, saying, “Oo,” na, we don't think, “No.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ja'a, Silas dènge Timotius dhu aj'a le miu lula-nèti Yesus Kristus, Ana Ama Lamatua. Nèngu dhu kapod'e-kabèli boe, peka na, &lt;&lt;oo&gt;&gt;, te ngaa a'abhu na, &lt;&lt;aad'o&gt;&gt;. Nèngu ne ub'a boe, te ladhe Na peka na, &lt;&lt;oo&gt;&gt;, a'abhu Na tare'a-re'a, &lt;&lt;oo&gt;&gt;.<bt>I, Silas, and Timotius have taught you-pl about Yesus Kristus, God's Child. He is not a deceptive (doublet) person who says “oo”, but means “no”. He also does not change, cuz (elaboration) if He says “oo”, His meaning really is “oo”.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari boe"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-20 03:17:56Z" status="Anyone">sonde geser</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 18:5</note><v n="20" />Madha j'ara aa'i-aa'i dhu Ama Lamatua pajaji tèke, èèna na Na paj'aj'i si. Nèti èèna ka, ladhe Yesus pamoa ca j'ara, peka na, &lt;&lt;oo&gt;&gt;, èdhi bisa dhaa, na, &lt;&lt;Tare'a! Lèke sèmi èèna!&gt;&gt; Lula ji'i nge'a le ngaa dhu Yesus neo tao. Ji'i peka j'ara ne, sèna ka pad'elo dadedha Ama Lamatua.<bt>Everything that God has promised, He will make happen/bring into being. That is why if/when Yesus promises something, saying, “oo,” we can respond, saying, “That's right. That's the way it is! Amin!” Because, we-exc already know beforehand what Yesus is going to do. We tell these things to show God's *glory (high-ness).</bt><v n="21" />Lamatua ne'e ka dhu hag'e nare miu dènge ji'i. Nèngu ka dhu ded'e nare èdhi, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu unu Na. Nèngu kahèi dhu tao èdhi taha taruu.<bt>God2 is the one who chose/selected you-pl and us-exc. He is the one who elevates/appoints us-inc to be His people. He is also the one who makes us-inc keep on enduring/persevering. [HCE, NLT]</bt><v n="22" />Nèngu ka dhu hia Roh Na, ho uri èdhi, aa pad'elo hia èdhi ngaa dhu Nèngu neo tao. Èèna nuka sèmi dhèu èci dhu tao tadha mi mèdha èci, sèna ka peka na, mèdha èèna unu nèngu.<bt>He is the one who gave His Spirit to oversee/organise/control us-inc, and show His plans to us. That is like a person places/puts his sign on some thing (physical) to show that it is his possession. [NOTE: because of UNS reponses, we needed to unmix topic and image of metaphor.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ja'a manèngi, sèna ka Lamatua mesa Na j'aj'i sakasii mi lii padhai ja'a ne. Te Lamatua ne'a d'ara ja'a. Nèngu ne'a, nga tao ka ja'a lake kore mèka dhiu asa Korintus. Ja'a ko'o boe pamakae miu, nèti èèna ka ja'a dhae dhiu mèka.<bt>I am requesting that God2 himself is the one who is witness to what I say here. Cuz (elaboration) He knows my insides (core being). He knows why it has not yet worked out for me to go to Korintus. I don't want to make you ashamed/embarrassed, so that is why I have not yet gone there.</bt><v n="24" />Ji'i ngo'o boe pakapai ngi'u j'aj'i dhèu kapai, ho laka-seti miu, peka na, miu hud'i parcaya mi cee. Te ngaa ji'i sab'a sama-sama dènge miu, sèna ka d'ara miu bisa karej'e-karae. Te miu bisa taha pa'èra, lula miu lèka Ama Lamatua.<bt>We-exc do not want to elevate ourselves as big/important people who force you-pl, saying, who you must believe/trust in. But we are working together with you, so that your livers can be happy/glad (doublet). Cuz (elaboration) you-pl can stand/endure firmly, because you-pl believe/trust in God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />De ja'a unu ku dhu pama'ète, na, ja'a bisa mèka dhiu ngad'o miu, sèna ka baku pabia miu aa'i-aa'i mi.<bt>So (consequently) I myself am the one who has decided that I am not yet able to go see you, so as to not burden you all (= cause anxiety, worry).</bt><v n="2" />Te ladhe ja'a pabia d'ara miu, na, cee hari ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara ja'a? Dhoka miu di. Te ngaa ladhe ja'a dhiu d'ara lai-lai ne, ja'a pabia miu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when I burden your insides, na, who else is there to make my insides happy? Only just you-pl. But, if I come quickly/right away, I would burden you. [DISCOURSE: higher-level context, and Hughes.]</bt><v n="3" />Nèti èèna ka, sasuri ja'a dhu uru èèna, peka na, ja'a lake kore mèka dhiu asa miu. Ja'a tatae era, sèna ka miu pamola mere ku lii langu miu. Hèia ropa ja'a dhiu, ja'a rasa bia heka, lula lii langu miu sèra. Te dhu lèke mola-mola, na, miu se ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara ja'a. Ja'a tadhe mèu miu se aa'i-aa'i mi. Ka ja'a ke'a mèu ladhe d'ara ja'a karej'e, na, d'ara miu sèmi èèna kahèi.<bt>That is why my previous letter, saying, it had not yet worked out for me to go to visit you-pl. I'm still waiting, so that you (can) finish straightening out/making right your issues/matters/disputes first. Then, when I do come, na, I won't feel heavy (sad, apprehensive) anymore about your issues. Cuz (elaboration ) in truth, you-pl there are the ones who make my insides happy. I know/understand all of you well/thoroughly. And/So I am sure/confident that if my insides are happy, na, your insides will also be happy like that. [NOTE: generally accepted that this other letter is NOT 1 Cor. see UBS TH “translating 2 Cor.” and Ex. Summ.; HCE, linking to context.]</bt><v n="4" />Lod'o ja'a suri sasuri dhu uru èèna hia miu, ja'a rasa susa dènge d'ara ja'a roe. Ja'a pahaa èi madha ae-ae. Te ngaa ja'a suri sèmi èèna, sèna ka miu me'a sasue ja'a mi dedha miu. Te ja'a suri boe j'ara ne, ho pasusa miu.<bt>When I wrote that previous letter to you, I felt troubled and weak/sad insides. I also wept many tears. But I wrote like that, so that you-pl could know/understand my love for you. Cuz (elaboration) I didn't write those things to disturb/trouble you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pabhèlu eele sasala dhèu<bt>Forgive (completely forget) people's wrongs</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(1 Korintus 5:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ètu talora juma'at miu sèra, abhu ca dhèu dhu pasusa d'ara dhèu ae. D'ara ja'a susa kahèi lula tatao dhèu èèna. Masi ka tatao nèngu ne lèke iia boe mi ja'a, te ngaa dhu lèke ae mi miu.<bt>In/among your congregation there, there is one person who has troubled/disturbed/distressed many people's insides. My insides are also troubled because of that person's deeds/behaviour. In actual fact, his doings really don't effect me too much, but they effect/impact some of you a lot. [NOTE to daughter translations: even though Corinth is far/remote from Paul, in Indo the convention for addressing those receiving a letter is ‘situ’ rather than ‘sana’.]</bt><v n="6" />Ja'a padhai lii pa'ae heka, te ae ka nèti miu dhu pasanèd'e nèngu le, hèia na ele-ho'a le.<bt>I don't need to say much more, cuz (elaboration) many of you have reminded/warned him, and he has already stopped/repented.</bt><v n="7" />De limuri ne miu pabhèlu eele ka sasala na, aa padhai lii pabe'a-be'a ka dènge ne. Te mage dhoka dhèu ne pakaj'èu iisi.<bt>So (consequently) now, you must completely forget (forgive) his wrong, and you must speak nicely/kindly with him. Otherwise he will withdraw/distance himself (from discouragement).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="limuri ne"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was ", limuri ne mi pabhèlu eele ka sasala na, aa padhai lii pabe'a-be'a ka dènge ne. Te, mage dhoka dhèu ne ele ngange"; Ours was " limuri ne mi pabhèlu eele ka sasala na, aa padhai lii pabe'a-be'a ka dènge ne. Te, mage dhoka dhèu ne ele ngange"; Theirs was ", limuri ne miu hud'i pabhèlu eele ku sasala na, aa padhai lii pabe'a-be'a ku dènge ne. Te, mage dhoka dhèu ne dara na ro"</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Nèti èèna ka, ja'a manèngi sèna ka miu pa'asu-pareo dènge ne, ho pa'èra d'ara na, peka na, miu sue nèngu taruu.<bt>That's why I request that you-pl gather (doublet) together with him, and assure him that you continue to love him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ja'a suri sasuri ja'a dhu uru èèna, ho neo uji miu. Te neo ke'a, na, miu tao dhu lèke, dènge tao madhutu aa'i-aa'i dhu ja'a paredha mi miu.<bt>I wrote my previous letter to test you. Cuz (elaboration) I wanted to know whether you were doing what is right/correct, and doing according to everything that I have commanded you.</bt><v n="10" />Ladhe miu tèka heka d'ara, aa pabhèlu eele sasala dhèu, na, ja'a madhutu kahèi ngaa dhu miu pama'ète mere le. Ladhe abhu sasala na dhu ja'a parluu pabhèlu, na, ja'a pabhèlu eele sasala dhèu èèna kahèi. Ja'a tao sèmi èèna ka ètu madha Kristus, sèna ka j'aj'i conto dhu be'a hia miu.<bt>If you don't store insides (=hate, resentment, desire for revenge) anymore, and completely forget (forgive) a person's wrong/sin, na, I will also go along with what you have decided. If there is a wrong (of his) that I need to forget/forgive, na, I will also forgive that person's wrong. I do that before Kristus, to be a good example (loan) for you-pl. [MC “example” from higher level context and purpose.]</bt><v n="11" />Te ja'a d'èi boe ladhe dhèu aae nidhu sii nare èdhi, sèna ka segi èdhi. Èdhi hud'i te'a ku naneo aapa nèngu. De baku pagoa iisi!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I don't like the king of the evil spirits to ensnare/trap us-inc, to defeat/conquer us. We must undersand his evil2/scheming plans. So (consequently) don't be stupid (lit: don't dumbify yourselves)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sahèdhe "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-20 04:08:42Z" status="Anyone">hiki, jerat ;</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-03 04:42:47Z">UNS young not know</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">D'ara Paulus mau boe ètu Troas<bt>Paulus' insides weren't at peace/calm in Troas</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Uru èèna, lod'o ja'a ètu kota Troas, ho aj'a dhèu lula-nèti Lii Lolo Be'a Yesus Kristus, Lamatua bhoke j'ara hia ja'a.<bt>Previously, when I went to the city of Troas, to teach people about Kristus' Good News, God2 opened the way for me.</bt><v n="13" />Te ngaa d'ara ja'a mau boe, lula ja'a paraga boe dènge ari ja'a Titus ètu nèi. Hèia ja'a palangu lii dènge dhèu parcaya ètu Troas sèra, ka pakèd'i asa propensi Makedonia.<bt>But my insides weren't at peace/calm, because I didn't meet my younger.sibling Titus there. So then I took my leave from the believers in Troas, and left for the province of Makedonia.</bt><note reference="2:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 20:1</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus ka hia èdhi segi<bt>Kristus is the one who makes us win/gives us victory</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Te ngaa, masi ka ja'a ètu mia èèna ka, ja'a manèngi makasi ae-ae mi Ama Lamatua. Te Kristus lab'a le j'ara-j'ara dhu bhelu-katub'a, ka Na segi le. Aa èdhi pa'èki dènge Ne kahèi. Nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua pad'elo taruu, peka na, èdhi j'aj'i dhèu unu Na. De ropa èdhi peka dènge dhèu lula-nèti Kristus, èèna nuka sèmi hèu mèngi èci, dhu dhèu aa'i-aa'i sangèd'u rare.<bt>But no matter where I am, I give many thanks to God. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus has opposed evil things/matters/issues, and He has already won. And we-inc are also bound/linked to Him. That is why God keep showing that we-inc are His people. So (consequently), when we tell people about Kristus, that is like an aromatic fragrance that everyone can smell.</bt><v n="15-16" />Uru-uru sèra, lod'o dhèu Yahudi tao korban tunu, sèb'u hèu gèmu na ca'e asa Lamatua, ho pakarej'e d'ara Na. Èdhi èci èèna kahèi dènge hèu mèngi èci, dhu pasanèd'e Lamatua lula-nèti Kristus. Te ngaa bagi mi dhèu cahag'e, èdhi èci èèna ka dènge hèu badha madhe. Te ladhe dhèu dhu mamuri pakaj'èu nèti Lamatua rèdhi mamuri èdhi, èèna pasanèd'e rèngu, peka na, bèli-camèd'a rèngu madhe, aa cèri eele nèti Lamatua. Te ngaa mi dhèu cahag'e hari, èdhi èci èèna ka dènge hèu mèngi èci. Te ladhe dhèu dhu mamuri mola rèdhi mamuri èdhi, èèna pasanèd'e rèngu tasa mera mia Kristus hia mamuri mi èdhi, aa pala-bagi hia rèngu mamuri toke d'ai mia-mia. Dhèu rai-haha cee ka dhu bisa ad'u-ue j'ara se aa'i-aa'i? Aad'o, sina ma?<bt>Previously, when Yahudi people made a *burnt sacrifice, the smell of its smoke ascended to God2 to make His insides happy. We are also like a fragrant smell that reminds God2 about Kristus. But to some people, we are like a foul smell (lit: the smell of a dead animal). Cuz (elaboration). if/when a person who lives far from God2 sees our-inc lives, that reminds them that they will die and be separated off/cut off from God2. But to some other people, we are like a fragrant smell. Cuz (elaboration) if/when a person who lives straight sees our lives, that reminds them how Kristus has *saved/given life to us-inc, and given life that never ends. What human is able to do all this? There is none, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sèb'u hèu gèmu"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-20 04:21:19Z" status="Anyone">asap bau wangi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Sanèd'e, te ji'i se sama boe dènge dhèu leo dhu aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Lamatua, sèna ka abhu oto nuka sèmi pahia-pahèli pake Lii Holo-Nori Lamatua. Ji'i se sèmi boe èèna! Ladhe ji'i padhai lii, dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa ladhe rèdhi iia-iia, peka na, ji'i aj'a-nori dènge d'ara mola. Lii padhai ji'i kapua nèti Ama Lamatua. Aa mamuri ji'i pa'èki dènge Kristus.<bt>Keep in mind that we are not the same as other people who teach God2's Words/Message so that they can get profit/benefit, like they are doing commerce (doublet) using God2's Words/Message. We are not like that! If/when we-exc are speaking, everyone can see clearly/openly that we are teaching (doublet) with straight/right insides. What we say is rooted/sourced from God. And our lives are bound/linked with Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu unu Lamatua dhu pakako Lii Pajaji Hiu<bt>God2's people who carry out the New Promise</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Baku pangee, na, ji'i mulai padhai lii padedha iisi. Aad'o! Tao-tao miu pangee, na, ji'i sama sèmi dhèu leo dhu parluu ngèti sasuri hia miu dhu manèngi, ho miu sèmi ji'i dènge be'a, heka ji'i bisa pakako sasab'a-la'a ji'i, do? Do, ji'i parluu manèngi sasuri sèmi èèna kahèi nèti miu, ho ngèti asa dhèu leo? Aad'o, si?<bt>Don't think that we-exc are beginning to boast elevating ourselves. No! Perhaps you think we are like other people who need to bring a letter to you-pl so you receive us well, before we can start carrying out our work, or (what)? Or, (that) we need to request a letter like that from you to take to other people? No, right?</bt><v n="2" />Te sasuri ijin ji'i dhu abhu le. Sasuri ijin èèna nuka miu se. Te ji'i nge'a j'ara ae-ae nèti mamuri miu. J'ara se dhu tèke le ètu d'ara ji'i. Dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa baca mamuri miu; nèti j'ara ne'e ra tadhe hua-hela nèti sasab'a-la'a èdhi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) our letter of permission/credentials already exists. That letter is you yourselves. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc know/recognise many things about your lives. Those things are stored away in our insides. Everyone can read your lives [NOTE: this is a metaphor they use]; from there they know/recognise the results of our-exc work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sasuri ij"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was ", sasuri ijin ji'i dhu abhu le. Sasuri ijin èèna nuka miu se. Te ji'i nge'a j'ara ae-ae nèti mamuri miu. J'ara se dhu tèke le ètu dara ji'i. Dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa baca mamuri miu; nèti j'ara ne'e, ra tadhe hua-hela nèti sasab'a-la'a èdhi"; Ours was " sasuri ijin ji'i dhu abhu le. Sasuri ijin èèna nuka miu se. Te ji'i nge'a j'ara ae-ae nèti mamuri miu. J'ara se dhu tèke le ètu dara ji'i. Dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa baca mamuri miu; nèti j'ara ne'e, ra tadhe hua-hela nèti sasab'a-la'a èdhi"; Theirs was ", ji'i abhu le, sasuri sèmi èèna. Sasuri èèna, nuka miu se. Te ji'i nge'a j'ara ae-ae nèti mamuri miu. J'ara se dhu tèke le ètu dara ji'i. Dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa baca mamuri miu; nèti j'ara ne'e, ra tadhe hua-hela nèti sasab'a-la'a ji'i."</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te dhu lèke le, na, miu nuka sèmi sasuri èci dhu Kristus suri nare le. Hèia Na pangèd'u mi ji'i. Kristus pake boe tinta ho Na suri sasuri ne, te ngaa Na pake Roh Mola-Mèci nèti Lamatua dhu Mamuri. Kristus kahèi dule boe Lii Lolo Be'a Na ètu hadhu kabela, nuka sèmi Ama Lamatua tao hia Musa. Te ngaa Kristus dule ètu d'ara èdhi dhu mamuri.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) actually you are like a letter that Kristus has written. And He entrusted (it) to us-exc. Kristus did not use ink (loan) to write that letter, but He used the *Holy Spirit of the God who Lives. Kristus also did not carve His Words/Message in flat stones, like God2 had done for Musa. But Kristus carved (it) in/on our-inc insides that live.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èi mèdhi"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 01:18:31Z" status="Anyone">tinta</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-03 05:16:38Z">Lii Pacele ; 1) coffee; 2) ink</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhu lèke"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was ", dhu lèke le, na, miu se nuka sèmi sasuri èci dhu Kristus suri nare le. Hèia Na pangèdu mi ji'i. Kristus pake boe èi mèdhi ho Na suri sasuri ne, te ngaa Na pake Roh Mola-Mèci nèti Lamatua. Kristus kahèi dule boe Lii Lolo Be'a Na ètu hadhu kabela, nuk"; Ours was " dhu lèke le, na, miu se nuka sèmi sasuri èci dhu Kristus suri nare le. Hèia Na pangèdu mi ji'i. Kristus pake boe èi mèdhi ho Na suri sasuri ne, te ngaa Na pake Roh Mola-Mèci nèti Lamatua. Kristus kahèi dule boe Lii Lolo Be'a Na ètu hadhu kabela, nuk"; Theirs was ", dhu te'a mèu le, na, miu se nuka sèmi sasuri èci dhu Kristus suri nare le. Hèia Na pangèd'u mi ji'i. Kristus pake boe èi mèdhi ho Na suri sasuri ne, te ngaa Na pake Roh Mola-Mèci nèti Ama Lamatua dhu Mamuri. Kristus kahèi dule boe Lii Holo Nori Na ètu hadhu kabela, sam"</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 24:12, Yermia 31:33, Yeskial 11:19, 36:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ji'i bisa parcaya mi Ama Lamatua, na, j'ara se'e mema lèke tare'a, lula Kristus ka dhu pad'elo sèmi èèna.<bt>We-exc can believe/trust God that all these things really are true, because Kristus is the one who has shown that.</bt><v n="5" />Ladhe dhoka nèti ngi'u ji'i mesa mi, na, ji'i se unu boe koasa ho ad'u-ue ngaa-ngaa. Te koasa dènge hak dhu ètu ji'i, kapua na nèti Ama Lamatua.<bt>If it were only from we ourselves, na, we have no power/authority to do anything. Cuz (elaboration) the power/authority and rights (loan) that we have, are rooted/sourced from God.</bt><v n="6" />Lamatua ka dhu ded'e ji'i j'aj'i dhèu sab'a Na, dhu lole dènge dhèu lula-nèti Lii Pajaji Hiu Na. Te ngaa Lii Pajaji Hiu Na èèna lula boe madhutu atora rupa-rupa, te ngaa lula-nèti dhèu pa'èki dènge Roh Mola-Mèci. Ladhe dhoka tao madhutu iia d'ara di atora sèra, èèna nuka sèmi d'ara rèngu dhu madhe le dènge unu boe mamuri dhu lèke, dhu ma'ète boe èèna. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu mamuri pa'èki dènge Roh Lamatua, nèngu unu mamuri dhu lèke.<bt>God2 is the one who elevated/appointed us-exc to be His workers who tell people about His New Promise. But that New Promise of His, is not about people only doing according to/just obeying various regulations/rules, but about people bound/linked with the Holy Spirit. If a person just blindly follows regulations, that is like their insides are already dead, and don't have true/real life that never ends2. But if a person lives connected with God2's Spirit, s/he has that true/real life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakadhai "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 01:27:30Z" status="Anyone">tahubung; connected tip to tip, like Cistine chapel</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-03 05:27:17Z">pakadhèi connected hand-in-hand ; sarob'e = gandeng = arm-in-arm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lii Pajaji"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "ai-lula Lii Pajaji Hiu Na. Te ngaa Lii Pajaji Hiu Na èèna lula boe madhutu atora rupa-rupa, te ngaa lula nèti dhèu pa'èki dènge Roh Mola-Mèci. Ladhe dhoka tao madhutu iia dara di atora sèra, èèna nuka sèmi dara rèngu dhu madhe le dènge unu boe mamuri dhu lèke, dhu ma'ète nèdhi boe èèna. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu mamuri pakadhai dènge Roh Lamatua, nèngu un"; Ours was "ula Lii Pajaji Hiu Na. Te ngaa Lii Pajaji Hiu Na èèna lula boe madhutu atora rupa-rupa, te ngaa lula nèti dhèu pa'èki dènge Roh Mola-Mèci. Ladhe dhoka tao madhutu iia dara di atora sèra, èèna nuka sèmi dara rèngu dhu madhe le dènge unu boe mamuri dhu lèke, dhu ma'ète nèdhi boe èèna. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu mamuri pakadhai dènge Roh Lamatua, nèngu un"; Theirs was "ula nèti Lii Pajaji Hiu Na. Te ngaa Lii Pajaji Hiu Na èèna, lula boe nèti dhèu dhoka tao madhutu atora rupa-rupa, te ngaa lula nèti dhèu pa'èki dènge Roh Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua. Ladhe dhoka tao madhutu iia dara di atora sèra, èèna nuka sèmi dara rèngu dhu madhe le, aa abhu boe mamuri dhu lèke, dhu ma'ète nèdhi boe èèna. Te ngaa, ladhe dhèu mamuri pa'èki dènge Roh Lamatua, nèngu abh"</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yermia 31:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Uru-uru sèra, ropa Ama Lamatua dule Atora Na ètu hadhu kabela sèra, èèna mema be'a seli eele. Te ngaa masi ka dhèu madhutu aa'i Atora sèra, rèngu pacèri era dènge Ama Lamatua. Ka ropa Musa sèmi nare Atora se'e, rèhu na kaha'a. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu Isra'el bisa boe ladhe patae rèhu na. Te ngaa nèbhu-nèbhu ka, kaha'a ne ele.<bt>Previously, when God2 carved His Regulations/Law on those flat stones (known info), that really was good/excellent. But even if a person does according to/obeys all those Regulations/Law, they will still be separated from God. So, when Musa had received that Regulations/Law, his face shone. That is why the people of Isra'el were not able to look at his face. But eventually, that radiance/light disappeared/dissipated.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ladhe patae"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 01:35:52Z" status="Anyone">menatap, lia agak lama sedikit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èèna mema"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "èèna mema be'a seli eele. Te ngaa masi ka dhèu madhutu aa'i Atora sèra, rèngu pacèri era dènge Ama Lamatua. Ka, ropa Musa sèmi nare Atora se'e, rèhu na kaha'a. Nèti èèna ka dhèu Israel bisa boe ladhe patae rèhu na. Te ngaa,"; Ours was "èèna mema be'a seli eele. Te ngaa masi ka dhèu madhutu aa'i Atora sèra, rèngu pacèri era dènge Ama Lamatua. Ka, ropa Musa sèmi nare Atora se'e, rèhu na kaha'a. Nèti èèna ka dhèu Israel bisa boe ladhe patae rèhu na. Te ngaa"; Theirs was "tatao èèna dadedha na kapai titu kèna. Te ngaa masi ka dhèu madhutu aa'i Atora sèra, rèngu pacèri era dènge Ama Lamatua. Ropa Musa sèmi nare Atora se'e, rèhu na kaha'a heo lo'a-lo'a. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu Israel bisa boe ladhe patae rèhu na. Te ngaa,"</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 34:29</note><v n="8" />De ladhe dhu suri tèke ètu hadhu bisa abhu kale'e sèmi èèna, na, tasamia hari dènge ngaa dhu Roh Lamatua tao tèke le ètu d'ara èdhi? Tatu risi hari, si?<bt>So (consequently), if what is written in stone can be flashy/impressive like that, na, how about with what God2's Spirit has placed/stored in our-inc insides? Surely that is even greater/more impressive, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bisa abhu"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was ", bisa abhu kale'e sèmi èèna, na, tasa mia hari dènge ngaa dhu Roh Lamatua tao tèke le ètu dara èdhi, se? Tatu"; Ours was " bisa abhu kale'e sèmi èèna, na, tasa mia hari dènge ngaa dhu Roh Lamatua tao tèke le ètu dara èdhi se? Tatu"; Theirs was ", abhu dadedha na sèmi èèna, na, tasa mia hari dènge ngaa dhu Roh Lamatua tao tèke le ètu dara èdhi? Tatu dadedha na"</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />De Atora ne paj'uj'u, na, èdhi hud'i pasae tare ku huku madhe, ho pacèri nèti Lamatua, lula èdhi tao boe madhutu Atora aa'i-aa'i sèra. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Atora ne èra taruu era nèti Lamatua. Te ngaa Roh Lamatua èra risi eele hari nèti èèna, te Nèngu ka pad'elo j'ara sèna ka èdhi pabe'a hari dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>So [shift], those Regulations/Law showed that we-inc must bear the punishment of death to be separated/cut off from God2, because we do not do according to all those Regulations. Even that being the case, nevertheless those Regulations/Law continue to remain firmly/amazing from God2 [CHECK phrasing w/UNSs]. But God2's Spirit is even more amazing, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who has shown the way so we-inc can be restored to a good/right relationship again with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="De, Atora"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "De, Atora ne paj'uj'u na, èdhi se hud'i pasae tare ku huku madhe, ho pacèri nèti Lamatua. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Atora ne èra taruu era nèti Lamatua. Te ngaa, Roh Lamatua èra risi eele hari nèti èèna, te Nèngu ka padelo j'ara sèna ka èdhi"; Ours was "De, Atora ne paj'uj'u na, èdhi se hud'i pasae tare ku huku madhe, ho pacèri nèti Lamatua. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Atora ne èra taruu era nèti Lamatua. Te ngaa Roh Lamatua èra risi eele hari nèti èèna, te Nèngu ka padelo j'ara sèna ka èdhi"; Theirs was "Atora se paj'uj'u na, èdhi hud'i pasae tare ku huku madhe, ka pacèri nèti Ama Lamatua. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Atora ne dadedha na kapai taruu era. Te ngaa, dadedha Roh Lamatua kapai risi eele hari, te Nèngu ka dhu padelo j'ara sèna ka èdhi bisa"</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />De Atora dhu uru èèna dhèu pangee, na, dedha titu kèna, limuri ne dadedha na sèmi heka uru èèna, te ne'e ne abhu le dhu dedha risi.<bt>So (consequently), those Regulations/Law that people used to think were great/high, now are not so great/glorious/high anymore, cuz (elaboration) now there is something that is even more glorious/high.</bt><v n="11" />Atora se dhu uru èèna, kaha'a nuka sèmi rèhu Musa, nèbhu-nèbhu ku heka kaha'a na ele. Musa dènge Atora se mema dedha tare'a, te ngaa dhu dedha risi hari, nuka dhu taha taruu dhu ma'ète boe.<bt>Those Regulations/Law's are radiant/flashy like Musa's face, which later its radiance disappeared. Musa and those Regulations/Law are still great/impressive/glorious/high, but what is more glorious/high is the one/thing whose greatness keeps on enduring/sustaining forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ji'i aa'i-aa'i mi nge'a mèu, na, Lii Pajaji Hiu Lamatua èèna taha taruu, dhu ma'ète boe ciki sa. Nèti èèna ka, ji'i padhai lii mola-mola dhu pa'abhe boe.<bt>We-exc are all sure/confident that God2's New Promise is going to endure on, without end. That is why we are speaking clearly/openly, without restraint/holding back.</bt><v n="13" />Ji'i tao boe sama sèmi Musa. Te nèngu hud'i pa'abhe ku rèhu na dènge bèla, sèna ka dhèu Isra'el bisa boe rèdhi rèhu na, ho re'a na, kaha'a èèna ele le, do dhae.<bt>We don't need to do the same as Musa. Cuz (elaboration) he had to cover his face with a cloth, so that the people of Isra'el couldn't see his face to know if/whether that shininess/radiance had gone/disappeared, or not yet.</bt><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 34:33-35</note><v n="14" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua tao ngangee dhèu Isra'el sèra topo. Te toke d'ai sange ne'e, ladhe rèngu baca ètu Sasuri Lamatua nèti Lii Pajaji dhu dhui èèna, nuka sèmi bèla èci dhu hutu nare kètu ra, ka ro'o boe nanene aa ro'o boe re'a. Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu bisa bhoke d'ara rèngu, sèna ka rèngu bisa re'a mèu. Dhodhoka Kristus mesa Na.<bt>But God made/caused the people of Isra'el to be dull in thier thinking. Cuz (elaboration) to this day, if/when they are reading in the *Scriptures about His Old Promise, that is like there is a cloth that covers their head, so they don't want to listen and don't want to understand. There is nobody else who is able to open/uncover their insides so they can understand clearly. Only just Kristus alone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="topo. "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 02:00:48Z" status="Anyone">tumpul</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao ngange"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "tao ngangee dhèu Israel se topo. Te, toke dai sange ne'e, ladhe rèngu baca ètu Sasuri Lamatua nèti Lii Pajaji dhu dhui èèna, nuka sèmi bèla èci dhu hutu nare kètu ra, ka ro'o boe nanene"; Ours was "tao ngangee dhèu Israel se topo. Te toke dai sange ne'e, ladhe rèngu baca ètu Sasuri Lamatua nèti Lii Pajaji dhu dhui èèna, nuka sèmi bèla èci dhu hutu nare kètu ra, ka ro'o boe nanene"; Theirs was "patopo kahadhu dhèu Israel sèra. Te, toke dai sange ne'e, ladhe rèngu baca ètu Sasuri Lamatua nèti Lii Pajaji Dhui èèna, nuka sèmi bèla èci dhu hutu nare kètu ra, ka ro'o boe nanene,"</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Toke d'ai sange ne'e, ladhe dhèu Yahudi baca Sasuri Musa, rèngu nanene, te ngaa re'a iia boe. Ne'e ne j'aj'i lula rèngu nanene pake boe d'ara ra, lula abhu dhu pa'abhe d'ara rèngu.<bt>To this day also, if/when Yahudi people read Musa's writings, they hear/listen, but they don't really understand. That is because they are not listening with their insides, because there is something that is covering up their insides.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Te ngaa ladhe abhu dhèu dhu mulai parcaya Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, na, Kristus ka dhu bhoke d'ara dhèu èèna, sèna ka nèngu bisa ne'a mèu. Èèna sama sèmi dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Lamatua, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nèngu bhoke eele le bèla dhu pahutu rèhu na.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if/when there is a person who begins to believe in our-inc Head Yesus Kristus, na, Kristus is the one who opens/uncovers that person's insides so that they can truly understand. That is like what is written in the Scriptures, saying, “He has opened/uncovered that cloth that is covering/hiding his face.”</bt><note reference="3:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 34:34</note><v n="17" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, lod'o Musa padhai lii, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua&gt;&gt;, sasoa na, Roh Ama Lamatua. Ladhe èdhi abhu le Roh ne, Nèngu tao èdhi j'aj'i mi dhèu bebas.<bt>In the Scriptures, when Musa spoke, saying, “Lord/Master”, he was meaning God's Spirit. If/when we-inc get that Spirit, He makes us become a free person. [EXEG: freedom from what? what is this freedom? (UNS); Ex. Summ shows commentaries are all over the place on this--so we keep it broad if we can get reasonable responses on this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu kai-beko"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 02:31:04Z" status="Anyone">idiom = orang terikat (Lena not know)</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dènge j'ara sèmi èèna, Na tao èdhi asa tabha èra, sama sèmi Nèngu. Rèhu èdhi parluu heka pahutu. Aa èdhi pangee dhoka dadedha Lamatua èdhi, te Roh Na ka dhu soru-bara èdhi.<bt>In that way, He makes us become increasingly strong/great/impressive/amazing, like Him. Our-inc faces don't need to be covered anymore. And we keep thinking about our Master's glory/high-ness, cuz (elaboration) His Spirit is helping (doublet) us like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mèdha kab'ua dhu tèke ètu d'ara èru rai<bt>Valuable/expensive things that are stored in a clay pot</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ama Lamatua ka dhu pad'elo le rasa kasia Na mi dedha ji'i. Nèti èèna ka, Na pua le ji'i ho lole dènge dhèu lula-nèti Lii Pajaji Hiu Na. Nèti èèna ka, ji'i taha taruu, dhu nge'a boe roe.<bt>God has shown His mercy/pity to us-exc. That is why He has sent/commissioned us to tell people about His New Promise. That is why we keep persevering/enduring, and don't give up/become soft/weak.</bt><v n="2" />De karèi nèti uru ka ji'i pama'ète ngare le, na: ji'i peka-padhai mola-mola, na, ji'i tao boe j'ara-j'ara bhabhelu-katub'a sama sèmi dhèu leo. Dhèu sèra tao pahuni-pahuni sèna ka dhèu baku ladhe rèdhi. Aa rèngu dhu re'a boe makae. Te ngaa ji'i ngo'o boe kapod'e dhèu. Ji'i kahèi padhai lii hèb'a hua boe lula Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua, te ngaa ji'i aj'a-nori dènge mola-mola madhutu ngaa dhu lèke. Dènge j'ara ne'e, dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa parisa unu ra lii padhai ji'i ètu madha Lamatua, aa nile unu ra, ji'i se dhèu sèmi ngaa sa.<bt>So (consequently) from long ago we-exc have decided like this: we have told/explained clearly/openly that we to not want to/are not going to do evil things like other people. Those people like to do (things/them) in secret, so people can't see (them). And they also have/know no shame. But we-exc don't want to deceive people. We also don't lie/b.s. about God's Words/Message, but we teach clearly/openly what is true. In that way, everyone is able to examine for themselves what we are saying before God, and assess/evaluate for themselves what sort of people we are. [EXEG: what does “before God” modify? Ex. Summ strong on it modifying “we commend ourselves”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ète ngare"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "ète ngare le, na: ji'i peka padhai mola-mola na, ji'i tao boe j'ara-j'ara bhabhelu-katub'a sama sèmi dhèu leo. Dhèu sèra tao pahuni-pahuni sèna ka dhèu baku ladhe rèdhi. Aa rèngu se dhu re'a boe makae. Te ngaa ji'i ngo'o boe kapod'e dhèu. Ji'i kahèi padhai lii hèb'a hua boe lula Lii Holo n"; Ours was "ète ngare le, na: ji'i peka padhai mola-mola na, ji'i tao boe j'ara-j'ara bhabhelu-katub'a sama sèmi dhèu leo. Dhèu sèra tao pahuni-pahuni sèna ka dhèu baku ladhe rèdhi. Aa rèngu dhu re'a boe makae. Te ngaa ji'i ngo'o boe kapod'e dhèu. Ji'i kahèi padhai lii hèb'a hua boe lula Lii Holo n"; Theirs was "'ète ngare le, na: ji'i peka padhai mola-mola, ji'i tao boe bhabhelu-katub'a sama sèmi dhèu leo. Dhèu sèra tao bhabhelu-katub'a pahuni-pahuni, sèna ka dhèu baku ladhe rèdhi. Aa rèngu se dhu re'a boe makae. Te ngaa ji'i ngo'o boe kapod'e dhèu. Ji'i padhai lii hèb'a hua boe kahèi, lula nèti Lii Holo N"</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ladhe dhèu ro'o boe sèmi rare Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua dhu ji'i aj'a sèra, rèngu laho kahèi, lula rèngu cèri eele nèti Ama Lamatua.<bt>If people don't want to receive/accept God2's Good News that we-exc teach, they come to ruin/things fall apart, because they are separated/cut off from God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dhèu aae nidhu, nuka sèmi lamatua èci dhu dhèu lasi sogo-tagu. Na ad'u-ue pa'ele iie kahadhu dhèu cahag'e, ka d'ara dhèu se j'aj'i maroga kiu-kiu. Rèngu se dhèu dhu parcaya boe Ama Lamatua èdhi. Lula rèngu bèdhu, bisa boe ladhe rèdhi saraa nèti Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka rèngu bisa boe re'a Lii Lolo Be'a lula-nèti Kristus. Rèngu re'a boe kahèi dadedha Kristus. Te Kristus ne, ca ropa dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>The king of the evil spirits is like a god (master/lord) who people are traditionally.worshipping. He makes some people's brains become dull, like they have become pitch dark in their insides. They are people who don't believe in our-inc God. Because they are blind like that, they are not able to see God's light. That is why they are not able to understand the Good News about Kristus. They also don't understand Kristus glory/high-ness. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus is the same model/type/kind as God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagu. Na"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was " tagu. Na ad'u pa'ele iie kahadhu dhèu cahag'e ka dara dhèu se j'aj'i maroga kiu-kiu. Rèngu se dhèu dhu parcaya boe Ama Lamatua èdhi. Lula rèngu bèdhu, bisa boe ladhe rèdhi saraa nèti Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka rèngu bisa boe re'a Lii Lolo Be'a lula nèti Kristus. Rèngu kahèi re'a boe dadedha dènge kapai Kristus. Te, Kristus ne"; Ours was " tagu. Na ad'u pa'ele iie kahadhu dhèu cahag'e ka dara dhèu se j'aj'i maroga kiu-kiu. Rèngu se dhèu dhu parcaya boe Ama Lamatua èdhi. Lula rèngu bèdhu, bisa boe ladhe rèdhi saraa nèti Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka rèngu bisa boe re'a Lii Lolo Be'a lula nèti Kristus. Rèngu kahèi re'a boe dadedha dènge kapai Kristus. Te Kristus ne,"; Theirs was "-tagu. Na patopo kahadhu dhèu cahag'e, hèia dara rèngu bhèdhu. Rèngu se dhèu dhu parcaya boe Ama Lamatua dhu tare'a. Lula rèngu bèdhu sèmi èèna, ra bisa boe ladhe rèdhi saraa nèti Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu bisa boe re'a Lii Lolo Be'a lula nèti Kristus. Rèngu re'a boe kahèi dadedha Kristus. Te Kristus ne,"</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ji'i padhai lii boe padedha iisi ji'i. Te ngaa ji'i padhai lii padedha Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Dhu ji'i padhai lula ngi'u ji'i dhodhoka sèmi ne'e di: nuka ji'i tao iisi ji'i nuka sèmi ana pua-paleha, sèna ka laladhe-leru miu lula ji'i j'aj'i dhèu unu Yesus.<bt>We-exc don't say a lot to elevate ourselves. But we talk a lot to elevate our Head, Yesus Kristus. What we say about ourselves is just this: we make ourselves like a servant to serve2/look after you, because we are Yesus' people. [NOTE: target lg requirement; can't say the Head, must be possessed “our Head”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boe padedh"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "boe padedha iisi ji'i. Te ngaa ji'i padhai lii padedha Yesus Kristus. Dhu ji'i padhai lai-lula ngi'u ji'i dhodhoka sèmi ne'e di: nuka, ji'i tao iisi ji'i nuka sèmi dhèu pua-paleha, sèna ka laladhe-leru miu"; Ours was "boe padedha iisi ji'i. Te ngaa ji'i padhai lii padedha Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Dhu ji'i padhai lula ngi'u ji'i dhodhoka sèmi ne'e di: nuka, ji'i tao iisi ji'i nuka sèmi dhèu pua-paleha, sèna ka laladhe-leru miu"; Theirs was "ae boe nèti ngi'u ji'i. Te ngaa ji'i padhai lii ae lula nèti Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Dhu ji'i padhai nèti ngi'u ji'i dhodhoka sèmi ne'e di: ji'i tao iisi ji'i sama sèmi dhèu pua-paleha, sèna ka laladhe-leru miu,"</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Uru-uru sèra Ama Lamatua dhu peka nèdhi le, na, &lt;&lt;Hud'i dènge ku saraa dhu heo ètu era maroga.&gt;&gt; Hèia Na tao saraa Na ho pasaraa d'ara èdhi. Te Nèngu d'èi pala-bagi èdhi saraa Na. Sasoa na, ropa èdhi pangee lula-nèti Kristus, èdhi sanèd'e kahèi dadedha Ama Lamatua.<bt>Long ago, God once said, “There must be light which shines in the dark place.” So He made His light to shine into our-inc insides. Cuz (elaboration) He likes to give His light to us. That means that when we-inc are thinking about Kristus, we are also remembering God's glory/high-ness. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><note reference="4:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 1:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Masi ka ji'i se dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa Lamatua hia mèdha dhu kab'ua ètu d'ara ji'i. Ne'e nuka sèmi dhèu èci tèke mèdha na dhu kab'ua ètu d'ara èru rai. Mèdha dhu kab'ua ne, nuka saraa Ama Lamatua. De dhu lèke ka, koasa dhu kapai dhu ji'i unu, mai boe nèti ji'i, te ngaa kapua na nèti Ama Lamatua.<bt>Even though we-exc are humans, nevertheless God2 has put/placed a valuable/expensive thing in our livers. That is like a person has stored away his expensive/valuable things in a clay pot. The expensive/valuable thing, is God2's light. So it's clear that the great/amazing power/authority that we have, is not rooted/sourced in us-exc, but is rooted/sourced in God. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. Inc-Exc in NT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", dhèu rai"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was " dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa Lamatua hia mèdha dhu kabua ètu dara ji'i. Ne'e nuka sèmi dhèu èci tèke mèdha na dhu kabua ètu dara èru rai. Mèdha dhu kabua ne, nuka saraa Ama Lamatua. De, dhu lèke ka, na koasa dhu"; Ours was ", dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa Lamatua hia mèdha dhu kabua ètu dara ji'i. Ne'e nuka sèmi dhèu èci tèke mèdha na dhu kabua ètu dara èru rai. Mèdha dhu kabua ne, nuka saraa Ama Lamatua. De, dhu lèke ka, na koasa dhu"; Theirs was " dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa Lamatua hia le mèdha dhu kabua ètu dara ji'i. Ne'e nuka sèmi dhèu èci tèke mèdha na dhu kabua ètu dara èru rai. Mèdha dhu kabua ne, nuka saraa Ama Lamatua. Te'a mèu, na, koasa"</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />De masi ka dhèu ènyi raruri ji'i ètu mia-mia, te ngaa ji'i taha taruu. Masi ka ji'i nge'a aa'i boe, te ngaa ji'i ele boe ngangee.<bt>So (consequently) even if/though people press/oppress causing difficulty for us-exc all over the place, nevertheless we- exc keep on enduring/persevering. Even though we don't understand everything, nevertheless we also don't give up/lose thinking.</bt><v n="9" />Masi ka dhèu paj'èra ji'i ae-ae, te ngaa Ama Lamatua pa'ana-lalu eele boe ji'i. Masi ka dhèu dhedhe ji'i, te ngaa rèngu bisa boe palaho ji'i.<bt>Even though people csuse us-exc lots of difficulty/trouble, nevertheless God does not abandon (doublet) us to be on our own. Even though people beat/attack/abuse us, nevertheless they are not able to completely ruin/destroy us-exc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pa'ana-lalu eele boe"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 03:06:01Z" status="Anyone">we are not orphaned</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Lula ji'i abhu j'aj'èra ae-ae, nèti èèna ka ladhe ji'i ètu mia, ji'i bisa lolo dènge dhèu, peka na, Yesus abhu j'aj'èra ae-ae kahèi, lod'o Na madhe. Te masi ka dhèu paj'èra ji'i rupa-rupa, te ngaa ji'i madhe boe. Ne'e ne pasanèd'e dhèu, peka na, Yesus mamuri taruu ètu d'ara ji'i.<bt>Because we-exc have experienced so much/kinds of persecution/torture, that is why wherever we go, na, we can remind people that Yesus also experienced so much/kinds of persecution/torture when He died. Cuz (elaboration) even though people beat/attack/abuse us, nevertheless we do not die. That also reminds people that Yesus is living on in our insides.</bt><v n="11" />Mema tare'a! Ae le mamuri ji'i dhu abhu j'aj'èra oe madhe, lula ji'i j'aj'i dhèu unu Yesus. Dènge j'ara ne'e, dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa re'a, na, Yesus pala mamuri dhu lèke mi ji'i, masi ka bèli-camèd'a ji'i madhe.<bt>That's right! Several times, we-exc who are living now, nearly died, because we were Yesus' people. In that way, everyone can know that Yesus is giving us real life, even if later we die.</bt><v n="12" />De masi ka lèpa limuri ji'i madhe, te ngaa ji'i madha'u boe padhue-padhai lula-nèti Kristus. Te ji'i sadia madhe sèmi èèna, sèna ka miu abhu mamuri dhu lèke.<bt>So (consequently), even if in the end we die, nevertheless we are not afraid to talk (doublet) about Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) we are prepared to die like that, so that you-pl can get/obtain real/true life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bege"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 03:21:37Z" status="Anyone">takut</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-03 07:18:26Z">UNS some not know [CHECK KM beger ~ weger]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua dhu suri, na, &lt;&lt;Lula ja'a parcaya Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ja'a padhai lii.&gt;&gt; Ngangee ji'i sama kahèi. Lula ji'i lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i lole ku dènge dhèu lula-nèti Yesus Kristus.<bt>In the Scriptures it is written, saying, “Because I believe in God2, that is why I speak.” Our-exc thoughts are also the same. Because we believe in God2, that is why we must speak (out) telling people about Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sasuri Lam"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "sasuri Lamatua dhu suri na, &lt;&lt;Lula ja'a lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ja'a padhai lii.&gt;&gt; Ngangee ji'i sama kahèi. Lula ji'i lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i padhai ku lole dènge dhèu"; Ours was "sasuri Lamatua dhu suri, na, &lt;&lt;Lula ja'a lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ja'a padhai lii.&gt;&gt; Ngangee ji'i sama kahèi. Lula ji'i lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i padhai ku lole dènge dhèu"; Theirs was "Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, dhu suri na, &lt;&lt;Lula ja'a lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ja'a padhai lii.&gt;&gt; Ngangee ji'i sama kahèi. Lula ji'i lèka Lamatua, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i lole dènge dhèu lula"</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 116:10</note><v n="14" />Ji'i nge'a, na, Ama Lamatua ka dhu pamamuri hari Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus nèti mamadhe Na. Èèna na Nèngu kahèi ka dhu pamamuri hari èdhi, lula èdhi pa'èki dènge Yesus. Bèli-camèd'a Ama Lamatua patitu èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti ètu madha Na, sèna ka sèmi nare èdhi.<bt>We-exc know that God is the one who brought back to life our-inc Head Yesus Kristus from His death. Later He is also the one who will bring us-inc back to life, because we are bound/linked with Yesus. In the future God2 will stand us all in front of Him, to receive us-inc.</bt><v n="15" />Lamatua tao j'ara se'e aa'i-aa'i, sèna ka soru-bara miu. Nèngu neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na kahèi mi dhèu dhu asa tabha ae. Èèna na lii manèngi makasi rèngu mi Lamatua asa tabha ae, aa ra mangaku dadedha Na kahèi.<bt>God2 does all these things to help (doublet) you-pl. He is also going to show His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity to people, who increase in quantity over time. Later their expressions of thanksgiving/gratitude to God2 will keep increasing, and they will also acknowledge/confess His glory/high-ness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi parcaya taruu Lamatua<bt>We-inc keep believing in God2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Nèti èèna ka, èdhi taha taruu, aa ele boe ngangee. Masi ka ngi'u èdhi asa roe-bhilu, te ngaa Ama Lamatua asa pa'èra d'ara èdhi nèti ca lod'o asa ca lod'o.<bt>That is why we-inc keep on enduring/persevering, and do not give up/lose thinking. Even though our bodies break down/decay/weaken (doublet), nevertheless God increasingly strengthens/encourages our insides each day. [EXEG: NRSV, CEV, TB, and ES all put a section break here, between vs.15-16.]</bt><v n="17" />Te madhutu ngangee èdhi, lod'o limuri ne èdhi dhu abhu sasusa rupa-rupa. Te ngaa èdhi hud'i sanèd'e ku, bèli-camèd'a Lamatua neo ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha. Nèti èèna ka èdhi hud'i te'a, na, ngaa dhu j'aj'i se'e dènge boe sasoa!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) according to our thinking, now we are experiencing various sorts of troubles/difficulties2. But we must remember that later God2 is going to *glorify (elevate way up high) us. That is why we know/understand what is happening now, as having no meaning/significance! [NOTE: “according to our thinking” is not an addition, but is linking this verse into the context of vs.4:16-5:1 and helps clarify the attitudinal contrast of “slight” with the eternal reality, as hinted at by NLT, CEV, and HCE. It's talking about perspective.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lod'o limu"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "lod'o limuri ne èdhi dhu abhu sasusa rupa-rupa. Te ngaa èdhi hud'i sanède ku, na bèli camèda Lamatua neo ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha. Nèti èèna ka èdhi hud'i te'a na, ngaa dhu j'aj'i se'e dènge boe sasoa"; Ours was "lod'o limuri ne èdhi dhu abhu sasusa rupa-rupa. Te ngaa èdhi hud'i sanède ku, na bèli camèda Lamatua neo ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha. Nèti èèna ka èdhi hud'i te'a, na, ngaa dhu j'aj'i se'e dènge boe sasoa"; Theirs was "sèmi ne'e: lod'o limuri ne èdhi abhu sasusa rupa-rupa, te ngaa èdhi hud'i sanèd'e ku, na, bèli-camèda Lamatua neo ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha. Nèti èèna ka, èdhi te'a na, ngaa dhu j'aj'i se, ngaa-ngaa tao boe"</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />De èdhi hud'i ngee paie-iie ku mi j'ara-j'ara dhu tèdhi mèka. Baku pangee dhoka mi dhu ladhe tèdhi di. Te j'ara-j'ara dhu ladhe tèdhi, taha boe nare nèbhu. Te ngaa j'ara dhu tèdhi mèka sèra ka dhu taha taruu, aa dhu ma'ète boe.<bt>So (consequently), we must consider/pay attention to things that are not visible/obvious. Don't just see things that are visible/obvious. Cuz (elaboration) things that are visible now, don't endure/last long. But the things that are not visible, they are what later will endure/last long forever/without end.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Te èdhi te'a, na, ngi'u aae ne, èdhi pake taha ètu rai-haha di, nuka sèmi paleo dhu èdhi patitu taha. Masi ka ngi'u aae èdhi ele iie, te ngaa èdhi baku pangee, lula Ama Lamatua dhu sadia tèke le era dhu be'a èci hia èdhi ètu sorga. Era ne'e, j'aj'i boe nèti pa'ue-ai dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa j'aj'i nèti pa'ue-ai Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, era ne'e taha taruu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc know our bodies (that we have) now, we use/wear temporarily in this world, like a tent/shelter that we have erected temporarily. Even though our bodies will later be destroyed/come to ruin/fall apart, nevertheless we don't need to worry, because God has already prepared a beautiful place for us in the heaven. Humans did not make that place, but God2 is the one who made it. That is why that place will keep on lasting/enduring.</bt><v n="2" />Te ngi'u aae èdhi ne roe-bhilu ètu rai-haha ne. Ka èdhi neo titu kèna abhu ngi'u hiu dhu èdhi pake ètu sorga.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) these bodies of ours are already tired/weak in this world. And we yearn to get new bodies that we will use/wear later in heaven. [NLT]</bt><v n="3" />Hèia ropa èdhi d'ai era nèi, èdhi sama boe sèmi dhèu dhu dènge boe mèdha-papake ètu ngi'u, te ngaa pake mèdha hiu ètu ua èdhi.<bt>So later when we have arrived there (remote), we will not be like a person who has no clothes on his/her body1, but will be wearing new clothes on our bodies2.</bt><note reference="5:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Abhu sasuri Lii Yunani, peka na, &lt;&lt;pake mèdha-papake&gt;&gt;. Te ngaa cahag'e suri na, &lt;&lt;bhoke mèdha-papake&gt;&gt;<bt>There are Yunani language writings that write, saying, “wear/put on clothes”. But there are also some that write saying, “take off clothes”.</bt></note>Te èdhi j'aj'i boe samanga di, te ngaa ètu nèi èdhi abhu ngi'u hiu kahèi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are not only just spirit, but we will get/obtain new bodies there (remote). [NLT]</bt><v n="4" />Ngi'u aae èdhi dhu ele iie ne, tao èdhi mangeta, lula rasa j'èra. Masi ka sèmi èèna, to'o boe madhe, ho tèke eele ngi'u aae ne. Aad'o! Èdhi neo abhu ngi'u dhu hiu, sèna ka tèke eele ngi'u dhui, gati dènge mamuri hiu dhu lèke.<bt>Our bodies that are coming to ruin/decaying now, make us draw a long breath [CHECK optional phrasing w/UNSs], because we feel troubled (sad/discouraged). Even that being the case, nevertheless we don't want to die and so get rid of this body. No! We want to get new bodies, so that we can leave behind our old bodies, replacing them with new life that is true/real. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangeta suu-suu"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-24 04:04:42Z" status="Anyone">tarik nafas pende-panjang (pant)</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ama Lamatua ne'e ka dhu pa'èra èdhi ho sèmi tare mamuri dhu hiu. Nèngu kahèi bagi hia èdhi Roh Na, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha nèti Lii Pajaji Na.<bt>God is the one who makes us ready to receive/accept that new life. He also gives us His Spirit, as a promise like a sign of His Promise.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Nèti èèna ka, èdhi taha dènge d'ara èra taruu. Èdhi te'a, na, lod'o èdhi mamuri era ètu d'ara ngi'u aae ne'e ne, èdhi pakaj'èu nèti Lamatua.<bt>Because of that, we-inc continue to endure with strong/firm insides. We understand that while we are still in our current bodies, we are far from God2.</bt><v n="7" />Nèti èèna ka èdhi mamuri dènge parcaya mi Ama Lamatua. Èdhi mamuri boe dènge ngaa dhu èdhi ladhe tèdhi ètu rai-haha ne di.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we live by/via believing/trusting in God. We don't live just by/via what we are able to see in this world.</bt><v n="8" />Te ngaa èdhi te'a tare'a-re'a kahèi, na, ladhe èdhi madhe tèke eele ngi'u aae ne, ho lati mamuri sama-sama dènge Ama Lamatua ètu sorga, na, tatu èdhi karej'e risi eele hari.<bt>But we are also sure/confident that if we were to die leaving behind our current bodies to go live together with God in heaven, na, surely we would be even happier.</bt><v n="9" />Masi ka èdhi mamuri taruu ètu rai-haha ne, do madhe ètu ne'e sèna ka mamuri ètu nèi, te ngaa dhu lèke ka, èdhi hud'i pakarej'e ku d'ara Lamatua. Te dad'èi èdhi kèna.<bt>Even though we continue to live on in this world, or we die here to live there (remote), nevertheless the right/important thing is that we make God2's insides happy. Cuz (elaboration) that is our desire.</bt><v n="10" />Baku bhèlu. Bèli-camèd'a dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i lasi paraga dènge Kristus. Nèngu ne'e ka dhu Pama'ète Lii Langu madhutu tatao dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri ètu rai-haha. Hèia Kristus b'ala dhu pamèci dènge tatao dhu dhèu ad'u-ue. Te Kristus ne'a, dhèu ne tao be'a do tao dhu karehe.<bt>Don't forget. Eventually everyone must meet/encounter Kristus. He is the one who Judges according everyone's deeds/behaviour/character who lives in the world. So (subsequently), Kristus will respond/repay/reward/revenge what is appropriate according to a person's deeds/behaviour. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus knows, whether that person has done good, or, done bad/evil. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mage bhèlu"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "Mage bhèlu. Bèli camèda dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i lasi paraga dènge Kristus. Nèngu ne'e ka dhu Pamaète Lii Langu, dhu dadoo tatao dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri ètu rai-haha. Hèia Kristus bala dhu pamèci dènge tatao dhu dhèu ad'u-ue. Te, Kristus ne'a, dhèu ne tao be'a"; Ours was "Mage bhèlu. Bèli camèda dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i lasi paraga dènge Kristus. Nèngu ne'e ka dhu Pamaète Lii Langu, dhu dadoo tatao dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri ètu rai-haha. Hèia Kristus bala dhu pamèci dènge tatao dhu dhèu ad'u-ue. Te Kristus ne'a, dhèu ne tao be'a"; Theirs was "Baku bhèlu. Bèli-camèda dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i lasi paraga dènge Kristus. Nèngu ne'e ka dhu Pama'ète Lii Langu, dhu dadoo mamuri dhèu aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne. Hèia Kristus bala dhu pamèci dènge tatao dhèu èci-èci. Te Kristus ne'a, dhèu ne tao dhu be'a,"</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 14:10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, lula Kristus<bt>We-inc can be in a good/right relationship with God2, because of Kristus</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pabe'a dèn"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, lai-lula"; Ours was "pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, lula nèti"; Theirs was "bisa pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, lula"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Lula ji'i nge'a, na, bèli-camèd'a Kristus parisa mamuri ji'i, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i madha'u, aa pakab'ua Ne. Ka ji'i sab'a pa'èra-èra ho pamako dhèu, sèna ka ra parcaya Kristus. Ama Lamatua dhu ne'a d'ara mola ji'i. Ja'a d'èi kahèi, ladhe miu me'a d'ara mola ji'i se.<bt>Because we-exc know that Kristus will examine our lives, that is why we fear and honour Him. And we are working hard to persuade/coax/cajole people to believe in Kristus. God knows our straight/pure insides. I also want for you-pl to know that our insides are straight/pure. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. #2.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", na, bèli"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was " na, bèli camèda Kristus parisa mamuri ji'i, aa ji'i hud'i madha'u, aa pakabua Ne. Nèti èèna ka ji'i sab'a pa'èra-èra ho pamako dhèu, sèna ka ra parcaya Kristus. Ama Lamatua dhu ne'a dara mola ji'i. Ja'a dèi kahèi, ladhe miu me'a dara mola ji'i se"; Ours was ", na, bèli camèda Kristus parisa mamuri ji'i, aa ji'i hud'i madha'u, aa pakabua Ne. Nèti èèna ka ji'i sab'a pa'èra-èra ho pamako dhèu, sèna ka ra parcaya Kristus. Ama Lamatua dhu ne'a dara mola ji'i. Ja'a dèi kahèi, ladhe miu me'a dara mola ji'i se"; Theirs was " na, bèli-camèda Kristus parisa mamuri ji'i, nèti èèna ka ji'i hud'i madha'u aa pakabua Ne. Ka ji'i sab'a pa'èra-èra ho pamako dhèu, sèna ka ra parcaya Kristus. Ama Lamatua dhu ne'a dara mola ji'i. Dadèi ja'a, ladhe miu me'a dara mola ji'i kahèi"</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ji'i padedha boe iisi ji'i ètu madha miu. Aad'o! Te ngaa ji'i dhoka hia miu j'ara dhu be'a, sèna ka miu bisa pakab'ua ji'i dhu dènge boe makae. Dènge j'ara sèmi èèna, miu bisa dhaa lii dhèu dhu hèb'a aae. Te rèngu dhèu dhu koa iisi lula sasab'a-la'a rèngu dhu dhèu ladhe rèdhi, aa te ngaa d'ara rèngu mola boe.<bt>We do not elevate/promote ourselves in front of you. No! But we are giving you a reason(s) so that you can boast about us-exc, without shame/embarrassment. In that way, you will be able to respond to those people who are boasting/big-mouthing. Cuz (elaboration) they are boasting3 about work results that people are able to see, whereas their insides are not straight/pure. [NLT]</bt><v n="13" />Ladhe miu pangee, na, ji'i se huj'u, hèia ji'i padhai lii sèmi èèna ho pakako sasab'a Lamatua. Masi ka miu me'a boe, te ngaa Lamatua ne'a. Ladhe ji'i padhai lii pake ngangee dhu mola, na, ji'i padhai lii sèmi èèna, ho soru-bara miu.<bt>If you-pl consider us crazy, we are talking like that to carry out God2's work. Even though you don't understand, nevertheless God2 understands. If we are talking using straight (coherent, logical) thinking, na, we talk like that to help (doublet) you. [NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kristus sue èdhi titu kèna. Ne'e ne ka dhu pa'èra d'ara ji'i, ho pakako sasab'a-la'a ji'i. Te ji'i parcaya, na, Dhèu èci, nuka Kristus, madhe gati dhèu aa'i-aa'i. Sasoa na, èèna sama sèmi èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti madhe tèke eele mamuri dhui, aa dhu dènge heka hak ngaa-ngaa ètu rai-haha ne.<bt>Kristus dearly loves us-inc. That is what strengthens/encourages our insides to carry out our work/responsibilities/mission. Cuz (elaboration) we believe that one Person, that is Kristus, died to replace/in place of every person. That means that it is like/the same as we have all died leaving behind the old life, and have no more rights at all in this world. [EXEG: Ex Summ #2, NLT + context. NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your rendering of Rom. 6:4.]</bt><v n="15" />Kristus madhe pala dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra, sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri ètu rai-haha ne, mamuri heka madhutu dad'èi mesa ra. Te ngaa rèngu hud'i mamuri madhutu dad'èi Kristus, lula Nèngu madhe le gati rèngu, hèia Na mamuri hari.<bt>Kristus died for all people, so that all people who live in this world, no longer live according to their own desires/passions anymore. But (now) they must live according to Kristus' will/desires, because He is the one who has died in their place/replacing them, and He came back to life.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />De karèi nèti deo ne'e, èdhi baku nile dhèu madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha. Masi ka uru èèna èdhi nile Kristus pake ngangee dhèu biasa. Te ngaa limuri ne, ji'i nile heka Nèngu sèmi èèna.<bt>So (consequently), beginning now, we should not assess/evaluate/judge people according to normal human desires/ways. Even though previously/formerly we ourselves assessed Kristus, using normal human thinking. But now we don't assess Him like that anymore.</bt><v n="17" />Nèti èèna ka, dhèu dhu pa'èki dènge Kristus j'aj'i le dhèu hiu, dhu unu mamuri hiu. Dhèu ne sèmi heka uru èèna, lula mamuri dhui na ele le. Te limuri ne, dhu hiu abhu le.<bt>That is why a person who is bound/linked with Kristus has already become a new person, who has a new life. S/He is not the same as before anymore, because his old life has disappeared completely. Cuz (elaboration) now, the new (one, life) already exists.</bt><v n="18" />Aa'i-aa'i se, Ama Lamatua ka dhu tao. Nèngu ka dhu padame, sèna ka èdhi bisa pabe'a hari dènge Ne, lula Kristus saku eele le sasala-sasigo èdhi. Hèia Na pangèd'u èdhi sasab'a, ho èdhi pad'elo j'ara sèna ka dhèu leo kahèi bisa padame hari dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>All this, God is the one who does it. He again is the one who made peace (in [damaged] relationships) so we-inc could be restored to a good/right relationship with Him, because Kristus has wiped away our wrongs/sins (doublet). So He also gives/entrusts work/job/responsibilities to us, so we also show the way so that other people can also be able to be restored to peace (in relationships) with God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Sanèd'e, te lod'o Kristus pea ètu rai-haha ne era, Ama Lamatua dhu pake Ne ho lere nèti dhèu padame hari dènge Ama Lamatua. De Nèngu ige heka sasala dhèu, ka rèngu dui heka hahuku nèti sasala. Hèia Na pua èdhi lati peka dènge dhèu, na, rèngu bisa pabe'a dènge Nèngu.<bt>Remember that when Kristus was still in this world, God was using Him to bring/lead people to be restored to a right relationship with God. So (consequently), He does not count/keep track of their wrongs anymore, so they don't carry/bear the punishment of those wrongs anymore. And He sends/orders us to go tell people that they can be restored to a right relationship with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Te èdhi j'aj'i duta Kristus. De Ama Lamatua pake èdhi ho tèti dhèu mai, sèna ka padame dènge Ne. Lula ji'i j'aj'i duta Kristus, nèti èèna ka ji'i manèngi miu kahèi, na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua d'èi titu kèna, ladhe miu pabe'a hari dènge Ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are Kristus' emmisaries/envoys/ambassadors (loan). So (consequently), God uses us to bring coming people, so that they are restored to peace (in relationship) with Him. Because we-exc are Kristus' emmisaries/envoys/ambassadors, that is why we also request/urge you, saying, “God2 is yearning for you to be restored to a right relationship with Him.”</bt><v n="21" />Kristus mesa Na tao nèdhi boe sala. Te ngaa Ama Lamatua hia Ne pasae sasala-sasigo èdhi. Lamatua tao j'ara ne hia èdhi, lula mamadhe Kristus bhoke j'ara, sèna ka èdhi bisa mamuri dènge d'ara mola, sama sèmi Lamatua d'ara mola kahèi.<bt>Kristus himself never did wrong/sin. But God made Him carry/bear our-inc wrongs/sin. God2 did that for us, because Kristus' death opened the way so that we could be able to live with straight/righteous insides, just like God2 also has a straight/righteous insides.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua tao dhu hua iia hia èdhi<bt>God2 does what is good/best for us-inc</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Lula ji'i sab'a sama-sama dènge Lamatua, ji'i pasanèd'e miu sèmi ne'e: Ama Lamatua pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na ae-ae mi dedha miu. De miu baku sèmi mere d'ara hua iia Na iia-iia d'ara.<bt>Because we-exc are working together with God2, we want to remind you-pl like this: God has shown His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity in abundance to you. So (consequently), you shouldn't accept/receive His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity lightly/pointlessly/trivially.</bt><v n="2" />Te ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na dhu suri tèke, peka na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Scriptures it is written, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ropa d'ai ka lod'o na, Ja'a nanene lii èu.<bt>“At just the right time, I heard your-sg voice/sound.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ja'a soru-bara èu kahèi, ropa Ja'a pala-bagi mamuri mi dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>I also helped (doublet) you when I saved/gave life to people.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">De nanene pabe'a-be'a! Ne'e ne, d'ai lod'o dhu hua iia èèna kèna. Te ne'e ne, d'ai lod'o Lamatua kèna ho pala-bagi mamuri mi dhèu.<bt>So, listen carefully! Right now is just the right time. Cuz (elaboration) right now is God2's day/time for saving/distributing life to people.</bt><note reference="6:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 49:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Nèti èèna ka, ji'i j'aga mamuri ji'i pabe'a-be'a sèna ka mamuri mola. Te ji'i ngo'o boe bhabhae dhèu dhu neo mai asa j'ara mamuri Lamatua. Aa ji'i neo padhai mola-mola kahèi, sèna ka dhèu baku pa'ele iie kolongara ji'i.<bt>That is why we must guard our lives carefully to live straight/righteous. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc don't want to be a barrier/hindrance to people who are wanting to come to God2's way of life. And we also want to speak straight/honestly, so that people won't speak ruining our-exc good name/reputation. [NLT]</bt><v n="4" />Aa aa'i-aa'i dhu ji'i sab'a, ji'i tenge j'ara ho pad'elo, na, ji'i dhèu sab'a dhu be'a nèti Ama Lamatua. De masi ka ji'i abhu susa, do paraga dènge j'aj'èra, do mamuri ètu d'ara talora aae patao-palaha, ji'i taha taruu.<bt>And everything we do, we make an effort to show that we are God's good workers. So (consequently), even if/though we get/encounter trouble/difficulty, or experience suffering, or are living in the midst of chaos (doublet), na, we just keep on enduring/persevering.</bt><v n="5" />Ji'i taha kahèi ètu d'ara lod'o dhèu gama ji'i, lod'o ra pamaso ji'i asa d'ara bèdho, lod'o ra patao-palaha, lod'o ji'i sab'a bia, lod'o ji'i abhu boe pasaruru musi madha, aa lod'o ji'i manganga.<bt>We also keep on enduring when people beat us up, when they (non-referential) throw us into prison, when people make disturbances/riots, when we are working hard, when we can't sleep, and when we feel hungry.</bt><note reference="6:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 16:23</note><v n="6" />Ji'i taha dènge d'ara mola kahèi. Ji'i nge'a ae lula-nèti Ama Lamatua. Ji'i taha dènge d'ara taleo. Ji'i tao dhu be'a hia dhèu. Ji'i soro tèke Roh Lamatua ator ji'i. Sasue ji'i mola-mola mi dedha dhèu.<bt>We also endure/persevere with straight/right insides. We know much about God. We endure patiently (lit: w/wide insides). We do good for/to people. We allow God2's Spirit to arrange/oversee/put in order us. We also really/genuinely (straight-straight) love people.</bt><v n="7" />Ladhe ji'i padhai lii, ji'i padhai dhu lèke, dhu nge'a boe monya. Ji'i sèmi ngare koasa nèti Lamatua kahèi, sèna ka tao dhu be'a. Ji'i nuka sèmi sordad'u dhu ngèd'u rèka dhu tesa nèti Lamatua, sèna ka lab'a musu, aa segi taruu.<bt>When we speak, we say what is true, and don't lie/b.s. We also receive power/authority from God2 to do what is good. That is like we are soldiers, who are holding complete weaponry from God2, so we war/battle against enemies, and keep winning/conquering. [NIV, NRSV]</bt><v n="8" />Ji'i taha kahèi masi ka dhèu pakab'ua, do pahahe ji'i; masi ka dhèu padhai lii pamanahu ji'i, do ra j'aga kolongara ji'i; masi ka dhèu monya, peka na, ji'i kapod'e-kabèli dhèu, do ra peka na, ji'i padhai lii dhu lèke.<bt>We also endure/persevere, whether people are showing respect to us, or, they are trashing our name/reputation; whether they are speaking to bring us down, or, they are guarding our good name/reputation; whether people are lying/b.s. that we are deceiving (doublet) people, or, they say that we are speaking the truth.</bt><v n="9" />Abhu dhu tadhe boe ji'i, te ngaa abhu dhèu ae kahèi dhu re'a ngara ji'i. Pèri-pèri hari kèna, ji'i se oe madhe, te ngaa ji'i mamuri era. Dhèu huku ji'i bia pèri-pèri hari kèna, te ngaa ji'i madhe boe.<bt>There are those who do not know/recognise us-exc, but there are many who do know/recognise our name/reputation. We have nearly died many times, but we still keep on living. They (non-referential) have punished us severely/heavily many times, but we don't die.</bt><v n="10" />Masi ka ji'i rasa bia, te ngaa ji'i karej'e-karae taruu kahèi. Masi ka ji'i dènge boe doi-dhari, te ngaa ji'i tao dhèu ae j'aj'i kaja ètu d'ara ra. Èèna nuka sèmi ji'i unu boe ngaa-ngaa, te ngaa ji'i unu aa'i mèu-mèu kahèi.<bt>Even though we are feeling heavy (sad, discouraged), nevertheless our insides are glad (doublet) continually. Even though we have no money, nevertheless we are making many people rich in their insides. That is like we have nothing whatsover, but we also get/obtain everything.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ji'i padhai lii paled'a-led'a hia miu dhu ètu kota Korintus ne. Aa ji'i sue miu tare'a-re'a.<bt>We spoke clearly/openly to you-pl in the city of Korintus. We also really love you.</bt><v n="12" />Ji'i pad'elo le sasue ji'i mi dedha miu dènge d'ara kateme. Te ngaa sasue miu mi ji'i kura, lula dènge boe d'ara kateme.<bt>We have shown our love to you without restraint/wholeheartedly. But your love for us is lacking, because it is not with your whole insides.</bt><v n="13" />De ja'a neo holo miu nuka sèmi holo ana-ana ja'a. Be'a risi miu sue ji'i dènge d'ara kateme.<bt>So (consequently), I am going to advise you like you are my children. It would be better/best if you love us without restraint/whole insides.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Baku pakadheb'e dènge dhèu dhu parcaya boe Lamatua<bt>Don't bind/get too close/intimate with people who don't believe in God2/Lord</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakadheb'e"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-26 01:57:54Z" status="Anyone">terlalu rapat; bergandengan; jang satu kaki</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Baku pakadheb'e dènge dhèu dhu parcaya boe Kristus. Te miu sama boe dènge rèngu. Dhèu parcaya dhu mamuri mola, sama boe dènge dhèu dhu lab'a Lamatua, de nia boe ladhe ra tenge j'ara ho sab'a pa'èci. Dhèu be'a dènge dhèu be'a boe, pantas boe pa'èci. Èèna nuka sèmi saraa bisa boe pa'èci dènge maroga.<bt>Don't bind yourselves/get too close/intimate (active, deliberate) with people who don't believe in Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl are not the same as them. Believers who live straight/righteous are not the same as people who oppose God2/Lord, so (consequently) it is not appropriate if they try to find ways to work united. Good people and bad people (=not good people) are not fitting/appropriate (loan) to be/become joined/united. That is like light cannot mix/join/unite with dark.</bt><v n="15" />Kristus bisa boe d'ara èci dènge dhèu aae nidhu, si?<bt>Kristus cannot reach agreement (=one insides) with the king of evil spirits, right?</bt><note reference="6:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii Yunani ètu ne'e suri na, <span class="Italic">Beliar.</span> Beliar ne, ra pija nèti lii Ibrani <span class="Italic">Belial.</span> Sasoa na, &lt;&lt;dhu bhelu, dhu karehe, dhu guna aad'o, aa dhèu aae nidhu&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Yunani language here writes <span class="Italic">Beliar</span>. That Beliar, they borrowed from the Ibrani language <span class="Italic">Belial</span>. It means, “what is evil, what is bad, what has no use, and king of the evil spirits”.</bt></note>Sèmi èèna kahèi, dhèu dhu parcaya Ama Lamatua abhu pusaka, te ngaa dhèu dhu parcaya boe abhu boe pala.<bt>In the same way also, people who believe in God get an inheritance, but people who do not believe (in Him) have no share/portion/part.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />De a'abhu miu, sa mia? Ele boe miu pangee, na, miu bisa lami asa d'ara èmu sabaj'a Ama Lamatua sèna ka pahaha iisi mi Nèngu, èle na lami sogo-tagu hari asa èmu sogo-tagu nidhu, do? Bisa boe, si? Te Lamatua èèna, Ama Lamatua dhu mamuri. Nèngu j'aj'i Kètu èdhi kahèi. Ka èdhi j'aj'i le sama sèmi èmu sabaj'a Na, lula Nèngu pea ètu d'ara èdhi. Te Lamatua suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na, peka na,<bt>So (consequently) what/how is your-pl thinking? Perhaps you are thinking that you can enter into God's house of worship to worship Him, and then go enter again into a house of traditional worship of the spirits, or (what)? That's not appropriate, right? Cuz (elaboration) the Lord/God2 is the God who lives. He is also our Head. And/So we-inc are also like His house of worship, because He is living in our insides. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has written in His Scriptures, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Èmu Ja'a ètu talora aae dhèu-dhèu Ja'a.<bt>“My house is in the midst of My people. [EXEG: Not addition. Gk is verbal figurative form of noun ‘house’ often glossed as “dwell, live” but also “fix one's home” NJB and “make one's home” TEV; following HCE to resonate with context of 16a “temple”. Lev. 26:11-12 NRSV, “I will place my dwelling in your midst,” NIV “I will put my dwelling place among you,”; Ez. 37:26-27 NRSV “will set my sanctuary among them forevermore. My dwelling place shall be with them,” NIV “I will put my sanctuary among them forever. My dwelling place will be with them;”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ja'a laku-mai nèti talora aae rèngu kahèi.<bt>I also enter-exit in their midst.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ja'a neo j'aj'i Ama Lamatua rèngu.<bt>I'm going to be their God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rèngu j'aj'i dhèu unu Ja'a kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>They will also be My people.”</bt><note reference="6:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 26:11-12, Yeskial 37:26-27, 1 Korintus 3:16, 6:19; Epesus 2:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Nèti èèna ka, Lamatua suri sèmi ne'e kahèi, na,<bt>That's why God2 also wrote like this, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Miu hud'i kalua nèti talora aae rèngu, aa pacèri nèti rèngu,<bt>“You-pl must come out from their midst, and be separate from them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sèna ka miu baku j'aj'i sama sèmi rèngu.<bt>so you are not the same as them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">D'ara miu hud'i mola-mèci.<bt>Your insides must be clean/pure/holy (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa miu hud'i pakaj'èu nèti aa'i-aa'i dhu pakaj'alu d'ara miu,<bt>And you must distance (yourselves) from everything that defiles/dirties your insides, [EXEG: The Gk /akathartos/ impure, unclean, polluted (spiritually, morally), defile (religiously); if the quote is taken merely physically, as an earlier version in KM, consider explicating further with the line in \ov to force the spiritual/religious reading (as in HCE). Isa. 52:11 NRSV “Depart, depart, go out from there! Touch no unclean thing; go out from the midst of it, purify yourselves, you who carry the vessels of the LORD.” NIV “(same)...Come out from it and be pure, you who carry the vessels of the LORD.”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dènge sèmi èèna, Ja'a sèmi kore miu dènge be'a.<bt>in that way, I will accept/receive you.</bt><note reference="6:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Ja'a neo j'aj'i Ama miu;<bt>I want to/am going to be your Father;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa miu j'aj'i ana-ana Ja'a.<bt>and you will also be My children.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Se'e se ka dhu Kètu èdhi peka tèke,<bt>These are the things that our-inc Head is saying.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèngu ka dhu unu Koasa Risi Aa'i.&gt;&gt;<bt>He is the one who is Most Powerful/Authoritative.”</bt><note reference="6:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:14, 1 Sejara nèti Isra'el dènge Yahuda 17:13, Yesaya 43:6, Yermia 31:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari pasue aa'i-aa'i! Lula Ama Lamatua padhadha tèke le ho pala-bagi èdhi j'ara se aa'i-aa'i, nèti èèna ka èdhi hud'i pamèu ku d'ara dènge mamuri èdhi. Baku tèke eele hahera ciki sa hèi ètu mamuri èdhi. Te èdhi neo sèna ka mamuri èdhi mola-mèci tare'a-re'a hia mi Ama Lamatua, sèna ka pad'elo, na, èdhi madha'u dènge pakab'ua Nèngu.<bt>Dear siblings! Because God has promised2 all these things to us-inc, that is why we must make purify our insides and our lives. We must not allow/permit even a little filth/defilement2 stay/live/remain in our lives (imperative). Cuz (elaboration) we want to live truly/really clean/pure/holy for God, to show that we fear and honour Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hahera "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-26 03:01:56Z" status="Anyone">kaj'alu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">J'ara dhu pakarej'e d'ara Paulus<bt>A matter/things that make Paulus' insides happy</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Hia ji'i tebho. Bhoke d'ara miu ho sèmi mere ji'i dènge be'a. Baku soro kabodho mi ji'i. Te uru èèna, lod'o ji'i ètu talora aae miu, ji'i tao ngèdhi boe sala ngaa-ngaa mi dhèu èci sa. Ji'i dadugu ngèdhi mèka dhèu ho ad'u-ue sasala. Ji'i kapod'e-kabèli ngèdhi mèka dhèu, sèna ka abhu oto nèti rèngu kahèi.<bt>Siblings! Give opportunity/chance/time to us. Open your insides to receive/welcome us. Don't turn your bqcks on us (=reject). Cuz (elaboration) previously, when we-exc were among you, we never did wrong to a single person. We never persuaded/coaxed/tempted anyone to do wrong/sin. We also never tricked/deceived anyone to get advantage/profit from them.</bt><v n="3" />Lii padhai ja'a ne, neo boe pèci sasala asa dedha miu. Te ja'a dhu peka le, na, ji'i sue miu. De tasa mera mia èèna ka, ji'i se dhu pa'èki dènge miu, masi ka ji'i madhe do mamuri.<bt>What I mean is not to try to accuse/pass blame to you. Cuz (elaboration) I have already said we-exc love you. So (consequently) no matter what, we are bound/linked with you, whether we die or we live. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. (fairly unanimous); CEV]</bt><v n="4" />Ne'e ne ja'a parluu heka pangee ae-ae, te ja'a lèka miu. Ja'a koa miu, aa miu pa'èra d'ara ja'a kahèi. De masi ka ji'i abhu susa rupa-rupa, te ngaa d'ara ja'a karej'e-karae taruu, lula miu.<bt>Now I don't need to worry anymore, cuz (elaboration) I believe in/trust you-pl. I also boast about you, and you also strengthen/encourage my insides. So (consequently), even though we encounter various sorts of difficulty, nevertheless my insides continues to be glad (doublet) because of you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Uru èèna, lod'o ji'i dhiu asa propensi Makedonia, ngi'u ji'i roe-bhilu. Te ji'i abhu susa nèti g'ana-kariu. Ji'i pab'ala d'ara lii dènge dhèu dhu parcaya boe. D'ara ji'i madha'u kahèi.<bt>[NOTE: can't force Paul's word play on “outside-inside” here.] When previously we-exc came to the province of Makedonia, our bodies were extremely tired doublet. Cuz (elaboration) we encountered troubles/difficulties/strife left-right. We were arguing/fighting/opposing people who don't believe. Our insides were also afraid.</bt><note reference="7:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 2:13</note><v n="6" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua ka dhu pa'èra dhèu dhu ele ngangee. Hèia Nèngu pa'èra d'ara ji'i, ropa Na pua Titus mai dènge ji'i.<bt>But God is the one who strengthens people who have given up/lost thinking/discouraged/depressed. So He strengthened/encouraged our insides when He sent Titus to come to us.</bt><v n="7" />Nèti mamai Titus ne'e ka d'ara ji'i èra hari. Te nèngu peka na, lod'o nèngu ètu nèi era, miu dhu pa'èra d'ara na. Lii lolo nèngu ne'e ka, pa'èra d'ara ji'i. Nèngu lolo kahèi, na, miu neo titu kèna mèdhi rèhu ja'a, aa miu manyasa kahèi lula lii langu dhu uru èèna j'aj'i ètu talora aae miu. Aa Titus peka kahèi, na, miu tenge j'ara ho soru-bara ja'a. Nèti èèna ka, d'ara ja'a karej'e-karae.<bt>Titus' coming now strengthened/encouraged our insides again. Cuz (elaboration) he gave a report, saying, when he was still there (remote), you-pl had strengthened/encouraged his insides. That report also strengthened/encouraged our insides too. He also told/narrated that you yearned to see my face, and you really felt regret/sorry with the matter/dispute/issue which previously had happened in your midst. Titus also told/narrated about your efforts to help/assist (doublet) me. That is why my insides are glad. (doublet) [NLT]</bt><note reference="7:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 2:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ja'a ke'a, na, isi sasuri ja'a uru èèna dhu pasanèd'e miu dènge lii sakaa, èèna ka dhu papèd'a d'ara miu. Te ngaa ja'a manyasa boe ja'a suri sasuri èèna. (Aa te ngaa lod'o èèna ja'a ako manyasa, ropa ke'a, na, nèti sasuri ja'a ka d'ara miu pèd'a, masi ka nare boe nèbhu.)<bt>I know that my previous letter that warned you harshly, really made you feel troubled/pained insides. But I don't regret writing that letter. (Whereas in fact at that time, I did regret a little, when I found out that my letter was making you troubled/pained insides, even though only for a short period.)</bt><v n="9" />Te ngaa limuri ne, d'ara ja'a karej'e. Ja'a karej'e boe lula uru èèna miu ètu d'ara susa. Aad'o! Ja'a karej'e lula lod'o èèna, sasuri ja'a dhu pamako miu sèna ka ele-ho'a. Hèia miu mangaku sasala miu, aa tèke eele j'ara-j'ara dhu karehe, sèna ka kabèli hari ho madhutu j'ara mamuri mola nèti Lamatua. Te Lamatua ka dhu tao miu manyasa. J'ara ne, nèti boe ji'i dhu tao miu j'aj'i maruru.<bt>But now, my insides are glad. I don't feel happy because you were feeling troubled at that time. No! I feel happy, because at that time, my letter was persuading/coaxing/cajoling you to stop/*repent. Then you acknowledged/confessed your wrongs/sin, and left behind the things that were bad, to turn back and follow God2's straight/righteous way of life. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who made you regretful. In that way it was not us-exc here who made you become chaotic/disrupted.</bt><v n="10" />Te ladhe èdhi manyasa ètu d'ara èdhi, madhutu dad'èi Lamatua, na, èdhi ae eele nèti tao j'ara dhu bhèlu, hèia lèpa hari madhutu j'ara mamuri dhu mola. Ne'e ne ka dhu pakaj'èu èdhi nèti hahuku Ama Lamatua, ka èdhi mamuri heka dènge d'ara manyasa taruu. Te ngaa ladhe èdhi dhoka manyasa ètu hèb'a di, sama sèmi dhèu ètu rai-haha ne, èèna na èdhi cèri eele nèti Ama Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when we feel regret in our insides according to God2's will, we stop doing evil things, and then turn again to follow the straight/righteous way of life. That separates/saves us from God2's punishment, so.then we no longer live with regret continually. But if/when we only regret with just our mouths, like people in this world, then we will be completely separated/cut off from God. [EXEG: last phrase, NLT plus Uma BT.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Miu pangee sèku! Lod'o miu baca sasuri ja'a, ja'a ke'a na, miu manyasa kahèi. Èèna palèke dènge dad'èi Lamatua. Ne'e ne ka pa'èra miu ho miu core eele bhabhèlu nèti mamuri miu. Miu roe-bhilu le ètu d'ara bhabhelu miu. Miu madha'u kahèi, mage dhoka manahu hari asa d'ara bhabhelu-katub'a. Miu neo mèdhi ja'a, aa pa'èra taruu ho tao j'ara be'a. Miu pa'èra kahèi ho neo huku dhèu dhu ad'u-ue sasala. Lula miu tao j'ara dhu lèke sèmi èèna, nèti èèna ka miu mola-mèci. Dènge j'ara ne'e, abhu boe dhu bisa pèci sasala asa miu.<bt>Have a think about this! When you-pl read that letter of mine, I knew that you were also feeling regret. That was matching/according to God2's will. That strengthened/prepared you to get rid of evil things from your lives. You-pl were already weakened/tired by your evil. You were also afraid, lest you might later fall into doing evil (doublet) again. You yearned to see me, and were ready continually to do what is good. You were also ready to judge/punish people who do wrong. Because you were doing what is right/correct like that, that is why you are clean/pure/holy (doublet). In that way, there is nobody who can accuse/blame you (of any fault). [HCE]</bt><v n="12" />De sasuri ja'a uru èèna, hia boe mi dhèu dhu tao bhabhelu, do, mi dhèu dhu lèke j'aj'èra nèti bhabhelu na. Te ngaa ja'a suri sasuri èèna hia miu, sèna ka ja'a pad'elo, na, lii padhai miu ètu madha Lamatua èèna tare'a-re'a. Aa miu tare'a-re'a sue ji'i.<bt>So (consequently), I didn't write my previous letter to that person who did evil, or to the people who were effected by his evil. But I wrote that letter to you-pl, so that I could show that what you were saying before God, was true/in earnest/sincere. And you were truly loving us-exc.</bt><v n="13" />Se'e se aa'i-aa'i ra pa'èra d'ara ja'a.<bt>All of these things (that I am referring to), strengthened/encouraged my insides.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Miu pa'èra d'ara Titus kahèi, sèna ka d'ara na bisa mera-milu. Sèra sa, asa pakarej'e d'ara ji'i.<bt>You also strengthened/encouraged Titus' insides, so that his insides could be calm/at peace (doublet). That also made our insides even happier.</bt><v n="14" />Ja'a koa-kad'iri miu ètu madha Titus, lula tatao miu dhu be'a. Ja'a peka kahèi dènge ne, na, miu pamakae mèdhi mèka ja'a. Te j'ara aa'i-aa'i dhu ji'i lolo ngèdhi dènge miu sèra lèke tare'a. Aa j'ara aa'i-aa'i dhu ji'i lolo dènge Titus lula-nèti miu lèke tare'a kahèi.<bt>I have praised (doublet) you before Titus because of/about your good deeds. I also told him, saying, you-pl have never shamed/embarrassed me. Cuz (elaboration) everything that we-exc have ever told/narrated to you is true. So (consequently), everything that we told Titus about you is also true.</bt><v n="15" />De lod'o-lod'o na ngee nèdhi tatao dènge lii padhai miu, sasue na mi dedha miu asa tabha. Aa nèngu sanèd'e kahèi ropa na dhiu asa miu, ka miu sèmi mere ne dènge be'a, te ngaa isi sasuri ja'a j'aj'i ngangee mi miu.<bt>So (consequently) each time he remembers what you have done, and what you have said, his love for you keeps increasing. And he also remembers when he went there, and then you received him well, but my letter also caused you concern. [EXEG: MC has a note that suggest “fear &amp; trembling” here means respect &amp; humility; NLT “respect and deep concern”; TNTC “respect”; LN “sense #3: reverence”.]</bt><v n="16" />D'ara ja'a karej'e-karae, lula ja'a bisa parcaya miu ètu madha j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra. De d'ara ja'a kabèdhi heka dènge miu!<bt>My insides are glad (doublet), because I can believe/trust you in everything. So (consequently), I don't need to worry about you anymore!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara ja'a kabèdhi heka"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-26 04:14:08Z" status="Anyone">no longer worried, ada keyakinan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Rèngu hia sumbangan dènge d'ara mola<bt>They give a money.gift/contributions with straight/right insides</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari pasue aa'i-aa'i! Dad'èi ji'i ka ladhe miu me'a mèu d'ara hua iia Ama Lamatua, dhu Na pad'elo mi dedha juma'at-juma'at ètu propensi Makedonia.<bt>Dear siblings! Our desire is for you-pl to really understand God2's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity, which He has shown to the *congregations (loan) in the province of Makedonia.</bt><v n="2" />Te masi ka rèngu abhu susa ae-ae, te ngaa d'ara rèngu karej'e taruu. Nèti èèna ka, masi ka rèngu unu boe ngaa-ngaa, te ngaa ra hia doi ae-ae dènge d'ara mola-mèci, ho soru-bara dhèu parcaya dhu abhu sasusa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even though they encounter lots of difficulties/trouble, nevertheless their insides are glad continually. That is why, even though they themselves are poor, nevertheless they still give a lot of their money with clean/pure (doublet) insides, to help/assist (doublet) other believers who encounter trouble/difficulties. [EXEG: all commentators agreed that chapters 8-9 are about money and giving (to those in need/difficulty), even though the Gk never uses the term ‘money’ in these two chapters. So a number of things are made explicit early to set the stage and provide high level cohesion. In this verse attitudes are tied to action, so it is not just about giving, but about being generous, overflowing, and doing it with abundant joy. So also in discussion with UNSs and MTTs, because of regional norms of giving stingily, grudgingly, with strings, and expecting quid pro quo, the consultant felt these explications (deng hati barisi and yang dapa susa) were appropriate for high level cohesion.]</bt><v n="3" />Ja'a bisa lole kahèi, na, dhu rèngu hia sèra, hia aa'i nèti dhu rèngu bisa hia. Aa ra hia risi nèti sèra sa kahèi. Abhu boe dhèu dhu laka-seti si.<bt>I myself am able to tell/narrate that they give everything they are able to give. And they give in addition to/beyond that too. There is nobody who forces them to do that.</bt><v n="4" />Rèngu mesa ra ka dhu tare'a-re'a manèngi, sèna ka ji'i bhoke j'ara hia si. Dènge j'ara ne'e, rèngu bisa abhu bagian ho soru-bara dhèu dhu abhu susa ètu Yerusalem.<bt>They themselves are the ones who really/truly/earnestly requested so that we-exc would open the way for them. In that way, they could have a share/portion/part to help/assist (doublet) believers who are effected by trouble/difficulty in Yerusalem. [NLT &amp; Ex. Summ (unanimous).]</bt><note reference="8:1-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 15:26</note><v n="5" />Uru èèna, ji'i sanao sèna ka ra tao sèmi ne'e, te ngaa dhu ra tao èèna, risi nèti dhu ji'i sanao! Dhu uru j'ara, rèngu hia mamuri ra asa Ama Lamatua. Hèia ra peka kahèi, na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i neo soro mamuri ji'i, sèna ka lalau-lalo'o miu, lula èèna ka dhu madhutu dad'èi Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously, we-exc had been hoping they would do this, but what they have/are doing, is more than what we were hoping! First, they gave/turned over their lives to God. Then, they spoke further, saying, “We are going to turn over/surrender/dedicate ourselves to serve (doublet) you-pl, because that is according to God2's will.” [EXEG: ‘layani’ is actually further fleshing out Gk diakonias which is slightly undertranslated in KM vs. 4, and necessary from UNS responses to explain what “gave themselves … to us” means.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Lula conto nèti juma'at-juma'at ètu Makedonia sèmi èèna, nèti èèna ka ji'i manèngi Titus lèpa hari asa miu ètu Korintus, sèna ka miu soru-bara kahèi dhèu unu Lamatua dhu abhu sasusa ètu Yerusalem. Te uru èèna, nèngu ka dhu mulai pakaboko doi-dhari ho hia si. Hèia limuri ne, ji'i manèngi sèna ka nèngu bisa tao pamèci sasab'a-la'a miu ho soru-bara dhèu.<bt>Because of the example of the congregations in Makedonia, that is why we-exc are requesting that Titus return to you-pl in Korintus again, so that you also can help God's people who are in difficulty in Yerusalem. Cuz (elaboration) previously, he is the one who began to collect money to give them. So now, we are requesting for him to be able to finish/make complete your work/responsibility/mission of helping/assisting people. [NLT] [EXEG: Fleshed out to make referent tracking and time frame clearer.]</bt><note reference="8:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Titus 2:14</note><v n="7" />Sasab'a miu hia Ama Lamatua èèna, be'a titu kèna. Conto sèmi: parcaya miu èra, lii padhai miu be'a; miu me'a ae j'ara-j'ara Lamatua; miu sab'a dènge maj'èni; aa miu sue ji'i d'ai seli. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a neo ho miu soru-bara kahèi dhèu unu Lamatua dhu abhu sasusa, dènge j'ara hia si doi ae-ae.<bt>Your work for God2 really is very/exceptionally good. For example: your faith is strong; your speech/what you have to say is good; you know a lot about the things of God2; you work diligently; and you really (grammatical construction = superior degree) love us. That is why I want you to also help/assist God2's people who are encountering trouble/difficulty by/through giving a lot of money.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ja'a paredha boe miu ètu Korintus, sèna ka hia si doi ae-ae, te ngaa ja'a neo cob'a miu. Te juma'at-juma'at ètu Makedonia neo le soru-bara dhèu sèra. De dènge j'ara ne'e miu bisa pad'elo, na, miu tare'a-re'a sue dhèu dhu ètu d'ara sasusa kahèi.<bt>I am not ordering you-pl in Korintus to give a lot of money, but I want to test you (=test mettle, character, not school). Cuz (elaboration) the congregations in Makedonia are already wanting/going to help/assist these people. So (consequently), by this means you can also show that you really love people in difficulty. [NLT] [NOTE: Q: Add “sayang … sang orang susa di Yerusalem dong”? A: With restructuring of vs.6, and what is in vs.11, that would make it very heavy. My concern is by locking everything in to Jerusalem, local readers will not generalise a related application to themselves about giving to believers in difficulty. Let's leave some things broader.] [NOTE to daughter translations: In Gk the focus is on “genuineness of your love”, rather than “do you genuinely want to show your love”, but ALT: Jadi, beta mau tanya sang bosong di Korintus dong, “Kira-kira bosong ju mau kasi tunju batúl-batúl bosong pung sayang sang orang susa dong, ko?”]</bt><v n="9" />Te miu me'a, na, Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na mi miu. Mema Nèngu kaja. Te ngaa Na pama'ète nare ho tao iisi Na j'aj'i dhèu unu boe ngaa-ngaa sèna ka soru-bara miu, ho miu j'aj'i kaja ètu madha j'ara ae-ae.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you already know that our Head Yesus Kristus has shown His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you. Previously, He was a rich person. But He chose to make himself become a poor person to help/assist (doublet) you-pl, so that you could become rich in many things.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ranga-jahi na, miu mulai pakaboko le doi ho hia rèngu. Mesa boe miu hia doi-dhari di, te ngaa miu soru-bara nèti d'ara miu kahèi. De madhutu a'abhu ja'a, miu hud'i tao ku sèmi ne'e:<bt>Last year, You had already begun to collect money for them. You did not only just give money, but you helped/assisted from your insides too. So (consequently), according to my opinion, this is what you should do: [EXEG: I don't think there is a textual basis for saying “you (in Corinth) were the group that first thought to help those in Jerusalem” (even thought NLT and Uma BT say that, I think it is noise leftover from the KJV misrendering of Gk “previously began”] [EXEG: What is the basis for /bantu dari bosong pung hati/? /Dari/ goes to manner/ motivation, which is the focus of vs.8-9. Consultant felt it was appropriate reflection/ explication/ reinforcement of vague “the doing” in vs.10.] [NOTE: OV /Su mulai bantu/ implies money or assistance actually given, whereas the point Paul seems to be making is they began to collect it, but never a) finished collecting it, and b) never delivered it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ranga-jahi na"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-31 01:33:09Z" status="Anyone">taon lalu (flexible, TIME)</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Uru èèna, miu pama'ète mere le neo soru-bara dhèu unu Lamatua dhu abhu sasusa ètu Yerusalem nèi. De ja'a manèngi sèna ka ngaa dhu miu dhae pakaboko mere mèka, na, pa'oru aa'i si ho hia ka. Aa ca ngaa dhu miu bisa hia, na, hia laa. Dhu lèke ka, hia dènge d'ara kateme.<bt>Previously you had already decided to help/assist God2's people who encountered difficulty in Yerusalem (remote). So (consequently) I ask tbat what you have not yet finished collecting2, you gather it all and go ahead and give it to them. And however much you are able to give, na, just give (it, that). The important thing is, give wholeheartedly. [NLT, HCE]</bt><v n="12" />Te ladhe èdhi hia dènge d'ara kateme madhutu ngaa dhu èdhi bisa hia, èèna be'a kèna. Sad'i madhutu dad'èi èdhi. Te dhèu baku hia ngaa-ngaa dhu pabia nèngu, lula laka-seti nèti dhèu leo.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc give wholeheartedly according to how much we are able to give, na, that is good too. It'up to us-inc/our desires. Cuz (elaboration) a person shouldn't give what burdens/weighs him. by being forced what will later make things difficult for him. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: Te orang jang kasi apa yang nanti bekin susa sang dia, tagal kaná paksa.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ja'a d'èi boe pabia miu, sèna ka dhèu leo abhu samaa. Te dad'èi ja'a ka, èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti tago sama-sama sasusa dhèu se'e.<bt>It is not my intention to make things heavy/burden for you-pl, so that other people can be light(weight)/easy. Cuz (elaboration) my intention is for all of us-inc to carry together their trouble/difficulty.</bt><v n="14" />Te limuri ne, miu dhu unu risi, aa rèngu dhu unu ciki. Lod'o limuri, rèngu bisa b'ala kahèi, ladhe miu dhu unu ciki. Dènge j'ara ne'e, èdhi bisa tago sama-sama.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now you-pl have more/excess, and they have less/lack. Eventually they will also be able to repay/reciprocate, if you-pl later have less/lack. In that way, we-inc can carry (the load) together.</bt><v n="15" />Èèna nuka sèmi dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, na,<bt>That is like the Scriptures write, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu abhu ae,<bt>“The person who got/obtained much,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">risi boe nèti ngaa dhu rèngu parluu.<bt>did not get/have more than what they needed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa dhèu dhu abhu ciki,<bt>And the person who got/obtained a little,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kura boe nèti ngaa dhu rèngu parluu.&gt;&gt;<bt>did not get/have less that what they needed.”</bt><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 16:18</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Titus, dènge dhèu leo dhu neo rèti bantuan<bt>Titus, and other people who are going to deliver the (financial) aid (loan)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ja'a manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua, lula Nèngu ka dhu pamako Titus, sèna ka neo soru-bara miu, sama sèmi ja'a neo soru-bara miu.<bt>I give thanks to God, because He is the one who persuaded Titus to want to help/assist you, like I want to helpower/authoritysist you-pl.</bt><v n="17" />Mema ji'i manèngi sèna ka nèngu dhiu ngad'o miu. Aa te ngaa, èèna madhutu dad'èi nèngu mesa na. Nèti èèna ka, nèngu mesa na neo dhiu soru-bara miu, nèti boe lii manèngi ja'a.<bt>We really were requesting him to go see/check up on you. Whereas in fact, that was also his own desire. That is why he himself is the one who wanted to go help/assist you, not because of my request.</bt><v n="18" />Te ngaa nèngu dhiu boe mesa na. Te ji'i pua le a'ari ji'i ca dhèu, ho kako palere dènge ne. Juma'at aa'i-aa'i ètu ne'e tadhe mèu dhèu ne, lula nèngu sab'a bia ho peka-padhai dènge dhèu Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua.<bt>But he didn't go alone. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc have also sent/commissioned one of our siblings to go accompanying him. All the congregations here know/recognise this person, because he has worked very hard to tell people about God2's Good News.</bt><v n="19" />Kètu juma'at se dhu pili ne kahèi, ho palere-lere dènge ji'i, sèna ka soru-bara ji'i ètu d'ara sasab'a-la'a ji'i dhu hua iia ne. Ji'i pakako sasab'a ne, sèna ka pad'elo dadedha Lamatua èdhi, aa tao dhu be'a hia dhèu susa sèra ètu Yerusalem.<bt>The heads/leaders of the congregations have also chosen him to accompany us-exc, to help/assist us in this good work of ours-exc. We carry out this work, to show our-inc Lord/Master's glory/high-ness, and do what is good for those in difficulty in Yerusalem. [EXEG: Is this show God's glory? or glorify God? Gk genitive is vague enough that it could be either. In this context, it is most likely the latter [as in NLT]. But KM “botong kasi jalan ini karjá ko kasi tunju kotong pung Bos pung hebat” can carry both readings. Our protocol is where we can reflect the same ambiguities that are in the Gk, we should. Other problem: I'm not sure ALT “botong kasi jalan ini karjá ko angka tinggi-tinggi kotong pung Bos pung nama” makes any real sense in KM. CHECK.] [EXEG: OV do what is good for you there? or “do what is good for those in difficulty in Jerusalem? Gk is vague, but context clearly favours the latter (as in NLT, Uma BT).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ji'i tenge j'ara sèna ka tao dhu lèke, ho baku abhu dhèu dhu pasala ji'i, peka na, ji'i sab'a lèke boe lod'o ji'i ngèti doi sèra papala mi dhèu dhu parluu.<bt>We-exc look for ways to do what is right, so that there is nobody who is able to accuse us, saying, we don't work right/correctly when we take this money to the people who need it. [NOTE to daughter translations: Q: /cari jalan/ can imply uncertainty. A: Yes. On the one hand it nicely reflects the Gk “avoiding this, lest” “guarding against this, lest” - the point being they are taking deliberate and proactive steps to avoid any appearance or charges of corruption. I think CEV undertranslates on this point. On the other hand, KM /cari jalan/ might also be read as not having succeeded, although that was not the response from the UNSs. So ALT: botong usaha karás ko bekin yang batúl… (problem: usaha is often hard to reflect in daughter lgs).]</bt><v n="21" />Te ji'i pangee paie-iie, sèna ka tao dhu lèke nèti d'ara dhu mola-mèci ètu madha Ama Lamatua, aa ètu madha dhèu ae kahèi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we are thinking carefully to to what is right from/with a clean/holy/pure insides before God, and before many people too. [EXEG: Gk “regard for good things” is vague. Added “bekin yang batúl dari hati yang barisi” for clarifying higher level cohesion.]</bt><note reference="8:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Hini 3:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Abhu a'ari èci hari dhu ji'i pua dhiu palere dènge Titus si, ho rèti doi sèra. Ji'i ladhe paie-iie le mamuri nèngu. Aa ji'i nge'a, na, nèngu neo sab'a bia hia miu kahèi. Dhèu ne maj'èni, lula ne'a le, na, miu tao dhu lèke.<bt>There is another sibling whom we-exc are sending/commissioning together with Titus (collective) to take/escort that money. We have carefully observed his life. And/So we know he is also going to work hard for you. This person is diligent because he already knows that you are doing what is right. [EXEG: Q: is this brother here the same or different as the one mentioned in vs.18? A: Gk grammar is vague. The article says it is simply a known referent. So it could be anaphoric (the one in vs.18), or someone else who is known to the readers. Interpreting this is conjecture based on context. Ex. Summ. disappointingly does not address the question. NLT, CEV, TB2, TH, Uma, Hughes, all conclude this is a different person than the one in vs.18. Our protocols say we follow the TB in this situation. But it has to be introduced with a presentational clause, so this verse has been restructured from an earlier version.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ladhe dhèu karèi miu lula-nèti Titus, peka mi rèngu, na, Titus èèna a'ari ja'a dhu sab'a taruu dènge ja'a hia miu. Dhèu parcaya ètu era leo kahèi hag'e rare le dhèu rèngu, sèna ka rèngu kahèi rèti doi sèra asa Yerusalem. Rèngu pakaboko le ho neo dhiu. Titus sama-sama dènge rèngu kahèi. Rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra pad'elo dadedha Kristus sèmi èèna.<bt>If anyone asks about Titus, na, tell them that Titus is my sibling who is working with me continually for you/on your behalf. Believers in other places have also selected their (own) people, so they can take/bring this money to Yerusalem. They have already gathered wanting to leave. Titus is together with them. All of them will show Kristus' glory/high-ness like that. [EXEG: 8:6 says they are wanting Titus to come, so removed OV that he was in Korintus. “Already gathered with Titus” is from higher level context to make the transition from vs. 23 to 24 make sense. Q: Was the OV structure adequately reflecting 1st 3 words of the Gk? A: No. Restructured to do that. NLT, Ex. Summ.]</bt><v n="24" />De miu hud'i pad'elo sasue miu mi dhèu dhu rèti doi sèra. Aa pad'elo dènge ra, tasamia ka ji'i koa-kad'iri miu. Dènge j'ara èèna, dhèu-dhèu parcaya nèti juma'at ètu mia-mia re'a, na, miu sue rèngu.<bt>So (consequently) you-pl must show love to the people who take/bring that money. And show them why we-exc like to boast about you-pl. In that way, believers from congregations everywhere will know that you love them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Doi bantuan hia dhèu Kristen ètu Yerusalem<bt>Financial assistance/aid for the Kristen people in Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Dhu lèke, ja'a parluu heka suri hia miu, ho manèngi miu soru-bara dhèu parcaya unu Lamatua.<bt>Actually/in truth, I don't need to write any further, to request you to help/assist (doublet) God2's believers.</bt><v n="2" />Te ja'a ke'a le, miu d'èi titu kèna soru-bara dhèu sèmi sèra. Ja'a d'èi palolo dènge dhèu parcaya ètu Makedonia kahèi, lula-nèti babe'a d'ara miu. Ja'a palolo le, peka na, miu nèti propensi Akaya dhu pa'èra le karèi nèti ranga-jahi ni, ho pa'adhu doi bantuan. Ja'a lolo le kahèi, lula-nèti maj'èni miu ka dhu pamako dhèu leo, ho soru-bara dhèu-dhèu susa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I already know you are eager/have enthusiasm to help/assist people like that. I also like to/often tell the believers in Makedonia about your goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. I have told/narrated that you-pl from the province of Akaya were already prepared from last year [CHECK idiom] to send financial assistance. I also was telling/narrating about your diligence/enthusiasm2 that coaxes/persuades other people to want to participate in helping/assisting people in difficulty.</bt><v n="3" />Ka ja'a pua le a'ari èdhi, sèna ka ra pad'elo, na, ngaa dhu ji'i palolo lula-nèti miu se, leko-monya boe. Ja'a peka sèmi èèna, sèna ka miu pa'èra mema.<bt>And/So I also sent our-inc sibling(s) to show that what we-exc have told about you is not empty talk/lies/b.s. I tell (you) like that, so that you can be prepared beforehand.</bt><v n="4" />Te ladhe abhu dhèu Makedonia mai palere dènge ja'a, aa miu dhae pa'èra mèka, na, èdhi ta'e makae. Mage dhoka lalèka ja'a mi dedha miu dènge boe kolo-kapua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there are Makedonia people who come accompanying me, and then you are not yet ready, na, all of us-inc will be ashamed/embarrassed (lit: eat shame). May it not be that my faith/trust in you has no foundation/basis (idiom: tip-bsse).</bt><v n="5" />Nèti èèna ka, ja'a pangee, na, be'a risi ladhe a'ari èdhi dhiu uuru asa miu, sèna ka miu aa'i-aa'i mi bisa ator uuru ku doi bantuan sèra, madhutu lii pamoa miu uru èèna. Miu hud'i hia nèti babe'a d'ara miu, baku hia dènge d'ara cabèka.<bt>That's why I think that it would be better/best for our-inc siblings to go on ahead to you, so all of you can arrange/put in order that financial assistance according to your previous promise/commitment. You-pl must give from your goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity. Don't give stingily (lit: with half an inside).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèu-moke"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-31 03:14:28Z" status="Anyone">kikir</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dhu mola-mola, sèmi ne'e ka: &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu sèle hini ciki, èèna na abhu hua-hela ciki kahèi. Aa dhèu dhu sèle hini pa'ae-ae, èèna na abhu hari hua-hela ae-ae kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>What is straight is like this: “A person who only plants a few seeds, will later get a small yield/result. Ana a person who plants an (over)abundance of seeds, will later get back a high/bountiful yield as well.” [EXEG: Gk word choice here may indicate attitude as well as amount.]</bt><v n="7" />Ca dhèu-dhèu ka hud'i pama'ète unu na, nèngu neo hia ca ngaa. Baku hia dènge d'ara cabèka. Baku hia lula dhèu laka-seti. Te Ama Lamatua sue dhèu dhu hia dènge d'ara karej'e.<bt>Each person must decide on their own/for themselves, how much s/he wants to give. Don't give stingily/reluctantly (lit:w/half an inside). Don't just give because someone is forcing/pressuring. Cuz (elaboration) God loves the person who gives with happy/willing insides.</bt><v n="8" />Lamatua bisa hia miu mèngi-nale rupa-rupa. Nèngu bisa hia miu ae risi eele kahèi, sèna ka miu baku kura ngaa-ngaa. Te ladhe miu parluu, èèna na miu abhu risi nèti dhu miu parluu. Dènge j'ara ne, miu bisa papala dhu karisi, sèna ka soru-bara sasab'a aa'i-aa'i dhu nèti babe'a.<bt>God2 is able to give you various kinds of *blessings. He is also able to give you excess, so that you aren't lacking in anything. Cuz (elaboration) if/when you have a need, later you will get more than your need. In that way, you can divide out/share the excess to help all good work. [NOTE to daughter translations: samua karjá yang bae = “do all good work”; samua karjá deng bae = “do all work well”; careful the teams don't get sloppy.]</bt><v n="9" />Dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua, na,<bt>It is written in the Scriptures, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ama Lamatua d'èi pala-bagi hia dhèu unu aad'o,<bt>“God likes to distribute out to the poor people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nèti d'ara hua iia Na.<bt>from His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèngu tao dhu lèke taruu,<bt>He continues to do what is right/correct,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te d'ara mola Na èèna, taha taruu.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) His straight/righteous insides, endure continually.”</bt><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 112:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Lamatua ka dhu hia hini, sèna ka dhèu sab'a sèle oka-tedhe. Lamatua ka dhu hia nganga'a, sèna ka èdhi ta'a. Lamatua èèna kahèi, ka dhu hia miu mèngi-nale, ho miu bisa tao dhu lèke. Èèna sama sèmi miu dhèu sab'a oka-tedhe, hèia Lamatua hia miu hini, ho miu sèle. Aa hua-hela dhu miu abhu sèra, Lamatua hia hari ae-ae, nèti ca lod'o asa ca lod'o.<bt>God2 is the one who gives seed so workers can plant (them) in the gardens/fields (doublet). God2 is the one who gives food for us to eat. That same God2 is the one who later will give you-pl blessing(s) so that you can do what is right. That is like you are workers in the gardens/fields, and/so God2 gives seed for you to plant. And the result/yield/crop which you get, God2 gives many days, adds amount (=keeps increasing). [CHECK phrasing.]</bt><note reference="9:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:10</note><v n="11" />Te Lamatua neo pala-bagi hia miu risi nèti dhu miu parluu, sèna ka miu bisa soru-bara dhèu leo, dènge d'ara be'a miu. De ladhe miu soru-bara le dhèu leo, tatu dhèu se manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 wants to give you more than you yourselves need, so that you are able to help/assist other people with your goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. So (consequently) if/when you help/assist other people, they will give thanks to God.</bt><v n="12" />Te bantuan dhu miu hia mi dhèu unu Lamatua ètu nèi, tatu pasamaa si. Aa dènge j'ara ne'e kahèi, miu manèngi makasi mi Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that help/assistance (+financial) which you give to God2's people there, will surely help/assist (lit: lighten) them (i.e their burden/weight). And that also makes you-pl give thanks to God2. [EXEG: Q: Who will give thanks to God? A: Gk is vague, but this has to be looked at together with vs. 11. Gk in vs.11 clearly implies (they) will give thanks to God because of us (what we do). Vs. 12 could be either resulting in (you-pl) giving thanks to God, or (many people) giving thanks to God. We chose you-pl because one of the main points of vs. 6-10 (context) is the indirect benefit that comes back to the giver (here: the Corinthians).]</bt><v n="13" />Te lod'o miu soru-bara dhèu leo sèra, èèna j'aj'i mi tadha dhu peka na, miu parcaya tare'a-re'a. J'ara ne'e kahèi tao dhèu leo sèra koa-kio Ama Lamatua. Te rèngu bisa rèdhi dènge re'a, na, parcaya miu mi Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus leko-monya boe. Èèna, lula miu tao madhutu lalèka miu. Hèia ropa miu hia bantuan dènge d'ara kateme mi rèngu, aa hia mi dhèu leo kahèi, na, èèna ka dhu tao rèngu koa-kio kolongara Ama Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when you help/assist other people, that shows evidence/sign that you are believing in earnest/sincere/genuine. That also makes other people lift praises (doublet) to God. Cuz (elaboration) they can see your faith in Kristus' Good News is not empty talk/lies/b.s. That is because you are doing according to your belief. So, when you give help/assistance (+financial) from your wholehearted generosity to them and to other people as well, na, that is what makes them praise God's name/reputation.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Aa dhèu dhu sèmi rare bantuan nèti miu sèra, èèna na ra sabaj'a hia miu. Rèngu neo rèdhi miu kahèi, lula Ama Lamatua dhu pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na ae-ae mi dedha miu.<bt>And the people who receive the help/assistance from you, will pray for you. They also yearn to see you, because God has shown His abundant goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you. [EXEG: Q: shown to you, or shown through you (as NLT)? A: NLT1 is the only source that interpreted Gk epi as ‘through’ here. The normal dative for epi ‘upon’ is the sense of ‘to’ followed by other sources in Ex. Summ. Note NLT2 seems to have seen this as incorrect and have corrected it. So “used you to show His abundant grace to them” seems to be going beyond the text.]</bt><v n="15" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua ka dhu hia iia èdhi Hadia èci dhu be'a titu kèna, nuka Yesus! Kab'ua Na risi aa'i ngaa-ngaa! Nèti èèna ka, èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti sama-sama peka dènge Ama Lamatua, na, &lt;&lt;Makasi!&gt;&gt;<bt>But, God has already presented us-inc freely with a Gift that is too beautiful/pleasing/awesome. That is Yesus! His price/value is more than everything (else)! That is why all of us-inc together say to God, “Thank you!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus siri iisi na, lula sasab'a-la'a na hia Kristus<bt>Paulus defends himself because of his work for Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ja'a, Paulus, ka dhu suri sasuri ne. Tatu abhu nèti miu dhu pangee, na, ladhe ja'a sama-sama dènge miu, ja'a makae padhai lii paled'a. Te ngaa ladhe miu dènge boe ja'a, na, ja'a bani padhai lii dhu pa'abhe boe. Sèmi èèna ka, si? Aa te ngaa, ja'a dhu pasanèd'e le miu, na, Kristus ne dhu lii mako dènge d'ara hua iia mi dedha miu.<bt>I, Paulus myself, am the one writing this letter here. Surely there are those of you who think that if/when I were together with you, na, I would be shy/embarrassed/ashamed to speak clearly/openly/boldly. But if/when you are not (present) with me, I have the courage/boldness to speak without restraint. It's like that, right? Whereas in fact, I am the one who has reminded/warned you that Kristus' has been kind/gentle and good/gracious/generous to you. [NLT]</bt><v n="2" />Te ngaa abhu cahag'e nèti miu dhu ro'o boe nanene lii ja'a. Rèngu peka, tatao ji'i beda boe dènge tatao dhèu leo ètu rai-haha ne. De ladhe ja'a dhiu, ele boe ja'a padhai lii dènge rèngu pake boe pa'abhe. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a peka mema dènge miu aa'i-aa'i mi, sèna ka ladhe ja'a d'ai èèna, ja'a tao heka lii taka dènge rèngu.<bt>But there are some of you who don't want to listen to me. They talk, saying, what we do, is no different from other people in this world. So (consequently), when I go there, perhaps/probably I must speak without restraint/forthrightly to them. That is why I'm telling all of you beforehand, so that later when I arrive there, I won't need to speak harshly with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lii taka"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-31 04:08:21Z" status="Anyone">= lii sakaa; omong keras</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Masi ka èdhi se dhèu rai-haha, te ngaa ladhe èdhi pab'ala lii dènge dhèu leo, èdhi pakadhii boe, sèmi dhèu ètu rai-haha ne dhu tadhe boe Ama Lamatua.<bt>Even though we-inc are also humans, nevertheless if/when we are arguing with/opposing other people, we should not fight2/be nasty like people in this world who don't know/recognise God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakadhii"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-05-31 04:09:31Z" status="Anyone">kencang, tetap berkeras</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-04 04:37:06Z">pakadhi = bagigit</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ladhe èdhi patao dènge dhèu, baku bhèlu, te rèka èdhi sama boe dènge rèka dhèu rai-haha ne. Aa ladhe èdhi patao dènge dhèu kètu hadhu, na, èdhi unu koasa Lamatua, dhu bisa palaho ngangee rèngu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when we are fighting3/arguaing with people, don't forget, that our-inc weapons are not the same as people in this world have. And/So, if/when we are fighting3 with stubborn (lit: rock head) people we have God2's power/authority which can break down/apart/destroy their thinking/reasons/excuses.</bt><v n="5" />Koasa Lamatua bisa palaho aa'i ngangee dènge tatao dhu palab'a dènge Lamatua, dhu tao dhèu ho ro'o boe tadhe Lamatua. Koasa Nèngu kahèi bisa pad'elo j'ara, ho gati j'ara ngangee èdhi dhu dhui, dènge j'ara ngangee dhu hiu. Dènge j'ara ne'e, èdhi bisa pangee madhutu a'aj'a Kristus.<bt>God2's power/authority can dismantle/break down/apart every thinking/principle that opposes God2, which makes people not want to know/recognise Him. His power/authority is also able to show the way, to replace our-inc old way of thinking, with a new way of thinking. In that way, we can learn to think according to Kristus' teaching(s).</bt><note reference="10:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 12:2</note><v n="6" />Ae ka nèti miu mulai d'èi nanene Kristus, aa tao madhutu dad'èi Na aa'i-aa'i. Te ngaa abhu cahag'e nèti miu dhu ro'o boe nanene Ne. De ji'i dhu pa'èra le ho huku si.<bt>Many of you have begun to listen to/obey Kristus, and do according to His whole will/desires. But, there are some of you who still don't want to listen to/obey Him. So (consequently), we-exc are ready/prepared to punish them. [NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Miu d'èi laladhe ngaa dhu ladhe mèdhi ètu li'u di. Te ngaa miu hud'i ladhe ku d'ara dhèu. De ladhe dhèu pangee, na, nèngu dhèu pajuu-paleha Kristus, sanèd'e paie-iie, te ji'i se dhèu pajuu-paleha Kristus kahèi, sèmi nèngu.<bt>You like to just look at things that are visible on the outside. But you must look at a person's/people's inside(s). So (consequently) if/when there is a person who considers himself Kristus' *apostle (sent/commissioned one), na, remember/think carefully, cuz (elaboration) we-exc are also Kristus' apostles, like him.</bt><v n="8" />Ele boe miu pangee, na, ja'a padhai lii ae risi eele lula-nèti koasa dhu ji'i abhu nèti Lamatua. Sèmi èèna ka, si? Aad'o! Te Lamatua hia koasa èèna ho pa'èra miu, aa pa'ele iie boe miu. De ja'a soro tèke eele boe dhèu dhu pamakae ja'a, lula rèngu pa'ele iie sasab'a-la'a ja'a.<bt>Perhaps/probably you are thinking that I am talking excessivly big (boasting) about the power/authority which we-inc get from our Lord/Master. It's like that, right? No! Cuz (elaboration) God2 gives you-pl that power/authority to strengthen you, not to destroy/ruin/make fall apart you. So (consquently), I don't/won't allow a person to shame/embarrass me because they are dismantling/tearing apart and ruining My work. [NLT]</bt><v n="9" />Ja'a neo boe pamadha'u miu dènge sasuri ja'a sèra.<bt>It is not my intention to frighten you with my letters.</bt><v n="10" />Te ngaa dhèu sèra peka, na, &lt;&lt;Baku pusi-pahae dènge Paulus. Te masi ka isi sasuri na bia dènge sakaa, te ngaa ladhe patoo madha, nèngu roe aala-aala, aa lii padhai dhu dènge boe koasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But those people are talking, saying, “Don't care/be concerned about (doublet) Paulus. Cuz (elaboration) even if his letters are harsh and heavy/weighty, nevertheless if (we/you) are face-to-face, he is weak/powerless/soft, and his speech/what he has to say has no power/authority.”</bt><v n="11" />Te ngaa sèna ka dhèu dhu padhai lii omo koso sèra re'a, na, ngaa dhu ji'i suri ètu d'ara sasuri nèti kaj'èu, beda boe dènge ngaa dhu ji'i peka-padhai, ladhe ji'i ètu talora aae miu.<bt>But let those people who are empty talkng/lying/b.s.ing know/understand that: what we-exc write in a letter from afar, is no different from what we say if/when we come into your midst.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dhèu sèra sa d'èi padedha iisi, peka na, rèngu ka dhèu pajuu-paleha dhu kapai nèti Kristus. Ji'i bani boe pasoro ngi'u ji'i dènge dhèu sèmi sèra. Me'a, sina ma? Ele boe ji'i se èra boe sama sèmi rèngu! Dhèu sèmi sèra sa, dhodhoka tenge dhèu dhu sama sèmi rèngu di. Sèna ka rèngu pa'èra èci dènge èci, lula rèngu se ca ropa! Gagoa ra sèmi èèna ka!<bt>Those people also like to elevate themselves, saying, they are Kristus' impressive/great *apostles. We-exc don't dare compare ourselves with them. You understand, right? [=idiom signalling there is another meaning] It's surely not likely/there's no way we are strong/great2 like them! People of that sort, only just look for people who are the same as themselves. So that they mutually strengthen/support each other, because they are the same model/type/kind! How dumb is that! (idiomatic) [cf. 11:5; +irony]</bt><v n="13" />Aa te ngaa ji'i padedha boe iisi, ladhe dènge boe kolo-kapua na. Ji'i dhoka padhai lii sèmi èèna lula-nèti sasab'a dhu Lamatua pangèd'u mi ji'i. Ngaa dhu ji'i tao hia miu sèra, dhoka tao madhutu ngaa dhu Lamatua pua ji'i sab'a. Te ji'i sab'a boe dhu leo nèti èèna.<bt>Whereas in fact, we-exc ourselves don't boast if there is no reason/foundation/basis. We only talk like that about that work/responsibility which God2 has given2/entrusted us. What we have done for you, is only/merely in accord with what God2 ordered/commanded us to do. Cuz (elaboration) we don't work different than that.</bt><v n="14" />Dhu lèke ka, ji'i se padhai lii karisi boe, lod'o ji'i koa-kad'iri miu. Te ji'i ka dhu mai lole Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus hia miu. Ka miu sèmi mere lii padhai ji'i kahèi. Ladhe Lamatua pua boe ji'i, te ngaa ji'i koa-kad'iri miu, na, èèna mema lèke boe.<bt>In truth, we don't talk excessively/over the top when we are boasting (doublet) about you. Cuz (elaboration) we are the ones who came and told/narrated to you about Kristus' Good News. And you also accepted what we said. If God2 had never sent/commissioned us, but we were boasting about you, na, that would not be right.</bt><v n="15" />Ladhe dhèu leo ka dhu sab'a, na, ji'i padedha boe iisi, peka na, èèna rui-j'aj'èra ji'i na. Te madhutu mola-mola na, parcaya miu hud'i asa tabha èra. Dènge j'ara ne'e, rui-j'aj'èra ji'i ètu dedha miu karèi nèti uru ka asa tabha taruu.<bt>If another/different person is the one who does the work, na, we don't boast, saying, that was the fruit of our labours (idiom: from our suffering bones). Cuz (elaboration) what is important, is, your faith gets increasingly strong. In that way, the results/fruits of our work among you from before, will continue to increase. [NLT]</bt><v n="16" />Hèia ji'i bisa la'a peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus asa era-era dhu pakaj'èu nèti era miu, dhu abhu mèka dhèu sab'a ètu era sèra. Dènge j'ara ne'e, sasab'a ji'i patogo boe dènge sasab'a dhèu dhu ra pakako le ètu èèna.<bt>So/then, we are able to go tell Kristus' Good News in various places far from your place, which don't yet have anyone working there/that have no workers there. In that way, our-exc work doesn't/won't collide/conflict with the work of other people who have already been carrying out (his/their work) there. [NLT; NOTE to daughter translations: sphere can be 1) territorial, or 2) type of ministry (see NRSV “sphere of action” and LN “defined geographically and functionally”) Try to keep both interpretations open.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="patogo"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 01:09:05Z" status="Anyone">sideswipe, clash</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Te abhu ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua, dhu suri, na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe dhèu neo padedha iisi, na, hud'i padedha iisi dhoka lula-nèti Kètu èdhi, Ama Lamatua di.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Scriptures it is written, saying, “If there is a person who boasts, na, let him just boast about our-inc Head, God.”</bt><note reference="10:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yermia 9:24</note><v n="18" />Ladhe abhu ca dhèu dhu padhai lii dedha lula-nèti mamuri nèngu unu na, èèna sasoa na hèb'a-hua. Te ngaa ladhe Lamatua ka dhu koa-kad'iri dhèu ne'e, heka lèke kèna!<bt>If one person boasts about his own life, it's meaning is empty (doublet). But if God2 is the one who lifts praise about that person, na, now that's impressive! (idiomatic)</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu pajuu-paleha Kristus dhu mola, dènge dhu mola boe<bt>Kristus' *apostles that are straight/true, and those that are not straight/true</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Ja'a neo padhai lii sama sèmi dhèu goa. De miu nanene sèku! Lii ja'a sèmi ne'e ka:<bt>I want to/am going to talk like a crazy person. So (consequently) you-pl have a listen/try to understand! What I'm saying is like this: [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK ambiguity. In some lgs ‘talk crazy’ is different from ‘talk like a crazy person (=incoherent)’.]</bt><v n="2" />ja'a nuka sèmi ama miu, aa miu nuka sèmi ana bhèni ja'a dhu dhèu lii d'ai le. Dhèu dhu lii d'ai miu èèna, nuka Kristus. Ka ja'a ate sale boe miu, sèna ka ladhe d'ai lod'o miu kab'i, miu kalora iisi era. Hèia ja'a j'aga miu, sèna ka dhèu leo baku gagai miu, ho pa'ele iie parcaya miu.<bt>I am like your-pl father. You-pl are like my daughter who is engaged (to be married). The one who is like your fiancé is Kristus. So/and, I want to/am going to guard2 you carefully, so that later when the day of your wedding arrives, you are still clean/pure/holy. So (consequently), I guard you carefully so that there is nobody who bothers/harrasses you, to ruin/damage/spoil your faith. [Uma BT] [CHECK UNS: ate sale boe "selalu dlm perhatian"]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ate sale boe"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 01:23:04Z" status="Anyone">Idiom: selalu dlm perhatian; Lit: tidak salah kedip (mata)</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ne'e ne miu madhutu j'ara mamuri Kristus dènge d'ara mola. Te ngaa ja'a madha'u, mage dhoka dhèu tipu rare, miu sèna ka miu piku eele nèti j'ara mola èèna, nuka sèmi uru èèna mege tipu nare Hawa. Mege ne bisa tipu sèmi èèna, lula nèngu baki nèti kapod'e-kabèli!<bt>You-pl now are following Kristus' straight/righteous path with straight/pure insides. But I'm afraid lest there are people who deceive (successfully) you, so you deviate from that path, like that snake deceived (successfully) Hawa long ago. The snake could decieve like that, because he was the grandfather of deception!</bt><note reference="11:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 3:1-5, 13</note><v n="4" />Ladhe lod'o-lod'o miu paraga dènge dhèu sèmi sèra sa, ho ra aj'a-nori miu lula-nèti Yesus ropa leo dhu sama boe dènge Yesus dhu ji'i aj'a-nori miu, na, tasamia ka miu lèka lii padhai ra? Uru èèna, miu bhoke le d'ara miu ho sèmi mere Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua, sèna ka Na ator miu. Te ngaa tasamia ka limuri ne, miu neo hari sèmi mere roh ropa leo èci? Uru èèna, miu lèka Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus dhu ji'i aj'a miu. Te ngaa tasamia ka limuri ne miu parcaya hari a'aj'a ropa leo?<bt>Each time a person of that sort comes to you-pl, and then teaches you about a different model/type/kind of Yesus, that is not the same as Yesus whom we-exc have already taught you, na, why do you believe that person? [+challenge, rebuke] Previously, you opened your insides (welcomed) to receive/accept God's Holy Spirit for Him to oversee/arrange/guide you. So (consequently), why is it that now you want to receive/accept a spirit of a different model/type/kind? Previously, you believed in Kristus' Good News that we-exc told to you. But why is it that now you want to believe in a teaching of a different model/type/kind?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dhèu se padedha iisi ra, peka na, rèngu ka dhèu pajuu-paleha Lamatua dhu kapai risi. Madhutu ngangee miu, hak rèngu se risi nèti hak ja'a, do? Aad'o! Ja'a pake boe ngangee sèmi sèra.<bt>These people elevate/promote themselves, saying, they are God2's impressive/great *apostles. Perhaps (you think) their rights/authority are greater than my rights, or (what)? No! I don't go along with thinking like that. [Cf. 10:12]</bt><v n="6" />Masi ka ja'a d'èlu-mèu boe ètu d'ara lii padhai pake lii dedha, te ngaa ke'a mèu sasoa nèti ngaa dhu ja'a padhue-padhai. Miu dhu me'a le j'ara se'e, lula ja'a peka pahari-pahari le dènge miu.<bt>Even if I am not/were not skilled/clever in speaking using high language, nevertheless I cleanly understand the meaning/implications of what I'm talking about. You already know these things, because I have shown them to you repeatedly. [NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Lod'o ja'a aj'a miu Lii Holo-Nori Ama Lamatua, ja'a manèngi boe miu ogo-oru hia ja'a. Ja'a tao iisi nuka sèmi ana iiki sa, sèna ka bisa ded'e padedha miu. Teko-teko nèti j'ara ne'e ka miu neo pasala ja'a, do?<bt>When I was teaching God's Words/Teachings to you, I didn't request you to carry/be (financially) responsible for me. I made myself like a small/insignificant person/child, so that I could raise/lift you up. Perhaps (you think) you want to fault/blame/accuse me because of that, or (what)?</bt><v n="8" />Te dhèu parcaya nèti juma'at era leo sèra ka dhu tago ja'a, sèna ka ja'a bisa ladhe-leru miu. Ne'e èci èèna ka dènge ja'a kore nèti rèngu ho soru-bara miu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) believers from congregations in other/different places are the ones who carry/be (financially) responsible2 for me, so that I could serve/minister to you. That is like I take from them, to be able to help (doublet) you-pl.</bt><v n="9" />Lod'o ja'a bera-bera dènge miu, ladhe ja'a parluu ngaa-ngaa, na, ja'a manèngi boe miu, aa pabia boe miu. A'ari èdhi dhu mai nèti propensi Makedonia ka dhu soru-bara ja'a. Te ngaa ja'a pabia kèdhi mèka miu, aa bèli-camèd'a ja'a pabia boe miu sèmi èèna kahèi.<bt>When I am/was together with you, and if I had a need, I didn't request anything from you, and didn't burden you. Our-inc siblings who came from the province of Makedonia were the ones who helped/assisted me. But I never burdened you with anything, and I also am not going to burden you like that in the future (tomorrow-next day = common usage).</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Pilipi 4:15-18</note><v n="10" />Lii Holo-Nori Kristus ne lèke tare'a-re'a. Ja'a lèka mèu, na, lii padhai ja'a lèke kahèi, lula ja'a pa'èki dènge Kristus. Abhu boe ca dhèu sa ètu propensi Akaya dhu bisa kutu hèb'a ja'a, aa kai ja'a sèna ka baku padhai lii padedha, peka na, ja'a pabia boe miu sèmi èèna.<bt>Kristus' Words/Message is true. I am also sure/confident that my words/message are also true, because I am bound/linked with Kristus. There is nobody in the province of Akaya who can shut my mouth, and forbid me to boast that I don't burden you in that way. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. #1] [CHECK UNS: kutu ~ hutu]</bt><v n="11" />Nga tao ka ja'a peka sèmi ne'e? Ele boe, lula ja'a sue boe miu, do? Masi ka miu pangee sèmi èèna, te ngaa Ama Lamatua ne'a, na, ja'a sue miu.<bt>Why do I talk this way? Perhaps this is because I don't love you-pl, or (what)? Even if you think like that, nevertheless God knows I love you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />J'ara-j'ara dhu ja'a tao kèdhi le, ja'a tao taruu. Dènge sèmi èèna, dhèu dhu tema padedha iisi, peka na, tatao rèngu sèra èci èèna ka dènge tatao ji'i, na, padhai lii rèngu dènge boe kolo-kapua.<bt>The thing(s) I have (ever) done, I am going to continue to do. In that way, people who like to elevate/promote themselves, saying, their deeds are the same as our-exc deeds, na, they have no basis/foundation.</bt><v n="13" />Rèngu peka, na, Lamatua ka dhu pajuu-paleha rèngu. Rèngu se, dhèu sab'a dhu d'èi leko-monya dhèu! Dhèu se tao iisi ra nuka sèmi dhèu pajuu-paleha dhu lèke nèti Kristus. Aa te ngaa rèngu se dhoka padhai lii hèb'a-hua!<bt>They say God2 is the one who sent/commissioned them. They are workers who like to deceive (doublet) people! They keep trying to make themselves like Kristus' true *apostles. Whereas in fact all that is just empty talk/lies/b.s.!</bt><v n="14" />Miu baku cag'ag'a! Te dhèu aae nidhu kahèi tao iisi na sama sèmi ana-ana pajuu Ama Lamatua nèti sorga dhu nèti saraa aa d'ara be'a.<bt>You should not be surprised! Cuz (elaboration) the king of the evil spirits keeps trying to make himself like God's *angels (underling) from heaven who brings light and/have good insides (grace/kindness, generosity). [NOTE: KM construction /yang bawa CHARACTERISTIC/ is also used in John's writings ‘water that brings life’ etc..]</bt><v n="15" />Nèti èèna ka, miu baku malaa ladhe dhèu sab'a na neo tao iisi ra nuka sèmi dhèu dhu sab'a dènge d'ara mola. Sanèd'e, te èèna na Ama Lamatua b'ala bhabhelu-katub'a rèngu.<bt>That is why you should not be surprised if his workers also keep trying to make themselves like a person who works with a straight/righteous insides. But be careful, cuz (elaboration) God will repay/reciprocate their evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu pajuu-paleha Kristus dhu lèke, pasae j'aj'èra rupa-rupa lod'o ra peka-padhai lula-nèti Lamatua Yesus<bt>Kristus' straight/true apostles bear/experience various sorts of suffering when they tell people about the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ladhe mo'o, na, ja'a padhai lii hari ciki sama sèmi dhèu goa. Te ja'a neo padhai lii padedha iisi ciki.<bt>If you-pl like, na, allow me to talk crazy a little further. Cuz (elaboration) I'm going to try and talk arrogantly a little. [NOTE to daughter translations--make consistent with 11:1.]</bt><v n="17" />Dhu ja'a suri padedha iisi ne, dhoka neo padhai lii sama sèmi dhèu goa sa. Te lii padhai ja'a ne kapua na nèti boe Lamatua èdhi.<bt>What I am writing now to elevate myself in this way here, is merely crazy talk. Cuz (elaboration) my speech/what I am saying here, is not rooted/sourced in our-inc Lord/Master.</bt><v n="18" />Abhu dhèu ae dhu d'èi ded'e padedha ngi'u ra madhutu tatao dhèu rai-haha ne. De ja'a neo padhai lii padedha iisi kahèi sama sèmi rèngu.<bt>There are many people who like to elevate/promote themselves according to the deeds/customs/behaviour of humans. So (consequently) I also want to boast in the same way they do.</bt><v n="19" />Te miu dhu pangee, na, ngangee miu mola ladhe paraga dènge ca dhèu dhu kahadhu bia, na, miu soro tèke ne, si?<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you-pl who think yourselves clear/straight/logical thinkers, if (you) happen to meet/encounter a heavy-brained person (idiom: slow witted), na, you just put up with it/them patiently/generous (attitude), right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahadhu bia"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 03:10:14Z" status="Anyone">simpleton, low IQ</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ladhe dhèu leo tao miu madhutu dad'èi rèngu, na, miu soro tèke si. Nuka sèmi: ladhe dhèu tao miu sèmi ènu sa, miu soro tèke ne, do? Ladhe abhu dhu mana'u mèdha miu, miu soro tèke ne, do? Ladhe abhu dhèu tipu miu, miu soro tèke ne, do? Ladhe dhèu tao iisi nuka sèmi dhèu kapai, aa pahahe miu nuka sèmi ana iiki sa, na, miu soro tèke ne, do? Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe abhu dhèu dhu tèb'e miu, na, miu soro tèke ne sène.<bt>If other people do things to you-pl following their own desires, na, you just let them/put up with them. For example: if there is a person who makes you/treats you as their slave, do you just let them/put up with them, or (what)? If there is a person who steals your belongings, do you just let them/put up with them, or (what)? If there is a person who decieves you, do you just let them/put up with them, or (what)? If there is a person who elevates themselves as an important person, and treats you with contempt as if you are an unimportant person, do you just let them/put up with them, or (what)? It's the same if there is a person who slaps you around, na, you just let them/put up with them.</bt><v n="21" />Te ngaa baku nasa! Te ja'a makae, lula ji'i roe aala-aala. Te ji'i lake ngare boe tao sèmi èèna, sama sèmi dhèu sèra tao mi dedha miu.<bt>But don't be angry! Cuz (elaboration) I'm ashamed/embarrassed, because we-exc are so weak/soft. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc are not capable of doing that, like those people who are dong that to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa ladhe rèngu neo padedha iisi lula ngaa sa, ja'a bani padedha iisi sèmi èèna kahèi. (Te ngaa baku bhèlu, te ja'a padhai lii sèmi dhèu goa na!)<bt>But if they want to boast about anything, I also dare to boast like that. (But don't forget, I'm talking crazy here na! [+obvious])</bt><v n="22" />Rèngu se dhèu Ibrani tare'a-re'a, do? Oo! Ja'a kahèi dhèu Ibrani. Rèngu dhèu Isra'el, do? Oo! Ja'a kahèi. Rèngu sèra ana-èpu Abraham, do? Oo! Ja'a kahèi.<bt>Are they a genuine/true Ibrani? Oo! [+yes, affirmation] I am also an Ibrani. Are they an Isra'el person? Oo! So am I. Are they Abraham's descendants? Oo! So am I.</bt><v n="23" />Rèngu sèra dhèu sab'a hia Kristus, do? Oo! Ja'a kahèi sèmi èèna. (Baku bhèlu, te ja'a padhai lii paleko ne!) Mema, ja'a peka na, ja'a sama sèmi rèngu. Aa te ngaa ja'a risi nèti rèngu. Te ja'a sab'a bia risi. Ra bèdho ja'a ae risi. Ra game ja'a ae risi. Ja'a kahèi oe madhe pahari-pahari ae risi nèti rèngu.<bt>Are they Kristus' workers? Oo! So am I. (Don't forget, cuz I'm talking hyperbole/over the top/excessive here!) Yes, I did say I was like them. Whereas in fact, I am more than they are. Cuz (elaboration) I work harder. People have jailed me more often. They have beat/whipped me more often. I have nearly died repeatedly many more (times) than them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paleko "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 03:23:49Z" status="Anyone">maen gila</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 16:23</note><v n="24" />Ètu d'ara adhe-aai dhèu ja'a, dhèu Yahudi, ra hake paparu ja'a lèmi hari. Lod'o-lod'o ra hake paparu ja'a, na, ra hake tèlu nguru ceo hari pake gui.<bt>In the hands of my own Yahudi people, they whipped me five times. Each time I was whipped, they lashed me 39 times.</bt><note reference="11:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 25:3</note><v n="25" />Tèlu hari, dhèu hake ja'a pake aj'u. Ca tèka dhèu pèci neo pamadhe ja'a. Ja'a molo dènge kapa tèlu hari. D'ara ca mèu ca mèda, ja'a leb'o-leb'o ètu d'ara dhasi.<bt>Three times people beat me with wood. One time they stoned me wanting to kill me. Three times my ship sank/drowned. I was floating/drifting on the deep sea one day-one night.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leb'o-leb'o"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 03:33:00Z" status="Anyone">terapung</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 16:22, 14:19</note><v n="26" />Ja'a laku kaj'èu asa mia-mia pahari-pahari. Ètu d'ara kakako ne, ja'a paraga dènge j'aj'èra rupa-rupa, dhu tao ja'a oe madhe. Nuka sèmi: nèti èi aae lala ètu d'ara loko aae, nèti parapo, nèti dhèu ja'a dhèu Yahudi, nèti dhèu Yahudi boe, aa nèti dhèu dhu tao ngi'u ra sama sèmi a'ari dhèu parcaya, aa te ngaa rèngu leko-monya. Ja'a oe madhe kahèi ètu talora lèu, ètu d'ara kota, dènge era dhèu pea boe.<bt>I have repeatedly travelled far to various places. On those journeys there were many dangers/sufferings that made me almost die. For example: from floods/flashfloods on big rivers, from robbers, from my own Yahudi people, from non-Yahudi people, and from people who made themselves out to be fellow believers, whereas in fact they were deceiving. I have almost died at sea, in the city, and in empty places. [STYLE: reordered to cluster similar categories (types of situations vs. types of locations).]</bt><note reference="11:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 9:23, 14:5</note><v n="27" />Ja'a sab'a bia, aa paraga dènge sasusa ae-ae. Lod'o ae ka dhu ja'a bisa boe bhèj'i. Ja'a manganga dènge koko-kamango kahèi. Pahari-pahari ku'a boe ngaa-ngaa. Abhu kahèi lod'o dhu ja'a unu boe mèdha-papake, ka maringi oe madhe.<bt>I worked hard/heavy, and I got various sorts of troubles/difficulties. There were many times I wasn't able to sleep. I have also been hungry and thirsty. There were many times I had nothing to eat. There have also been times when I have had no clothes, and experienced extreme cold (nearly dying from cold).</bt><v n="28" />Aa ladhe mo'o boe ige j'ara se'e, na, ige sèmi ne'e ka: te bèli-bèli ja'a j'aj'i ngangee kapai, lula ngee kèdhi a'ari èdhi dhèu parcaya dhu pakaboko ètu mia-mia.<bt>If you don't want to count all those things, na, then just count these: cuz (elaboration) every day I have great worries2, because I think/worry about all our-inc sibling believers who gather in many places.</bt><v n="29" />Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu rasa roe-bhilu dhu bisa boe sab'a ngaa-ngaa, na, sanèd'e ja'a. Te ja'a sèmi èèna kahèi. Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu dadugu dhèu-dhèu parcaya sèna ka tao j'ara karehe sama-sama dènge rèngu, na, ja'a makae, aa nasa.<bt>If there is someone who feels unable/incapable/inadequate to do something, na, remember me. Cuz (elaboration) I am also like that. If there is a person who persuades/coaxes/cajoles believers to following along doing wrong with them, I am ashamed, and angry. [EXEG: “burn”; MC says it means “shame” here, others say “indignant”, some say “angry”, “distressed”; NIC1 “shame and indignation”, ICC1 “shame and distress”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ladhe ja'a neo padedha iisi, na, be'a risi ja'a padedha iisi lula-nèti j'ara-j'ara dhu pad'elo raroe ja'a. Tare'a!<bt>If I have to boast, it's better that I boast about things that just show that I am weak/soft. That's right!</bt><v n="31" />Kètu èdhi Yesus, dènge Ama Na, Ama Lamatua re'a, na, ja'a monya boe. Dhu lèke, ladhe dhèu koa-kio Ne toke d'ai mia-mia.<bt>Our-inc Head Yesus, and His Father God, know that I am not lying. It is appropriate if/that people praise Him forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Conto nuka sèmi, uru èèna ètu kota Damsik, gubernur nèti dhèu aae Aretas pua dhèu mate ho kèpe ja'a ètu hèb'a tedhe kota.<bt>For example, previously/long ago, in the city of Damsik, king Aretas' gubernor ordered people to wait for me at the city gates/doors, so they could catch/arrest me.</bt><v n="33" />Te ngaa angalai ja'a pamaso ja'a asa d'ara karogo èci. Ka ra dulu ja'a dènge dhari re li'u tembok kota. Hèia gubernur kèpe nare boe ja'a. De sanèd'e, ladhe ja'a mesa-mesa ku, tatu bisa boe, si?<bt>But my friends put me in a basket. And/then they lowered me using a rope from the outer wall of the city. Then, the gubernor was unable to catch/arrest me. So (consequently) remember/think, if I was on my own, I couldn't do it/have done it, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karogo "><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-02 03:56:28Z" status="Anyone">anyaman dari lidi tuak/lontar yg balobang-balobang</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:32-33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 9:23-25</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus ladhe nèdhi ngaa èci, nuka sèmi tanila sa<bt>Paulus sees something, as if in a vision</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Ladhe miu mo'o, na, ja'a padedha iisi hari ciki, masi ka gaguna aad'o. Te ngaa ja'a neo peka dènge miu j'ara-j'ara dhu Lamatua èdhi pad'elo le dènge ja'a ètu d'ara tanila.<bt>If you-pl like, na, permit me to boast a little more, even though it is pointless/useless. But I am going to tell you things that our-inc Lord/Master has shown me in a vision.</bt><v n="2-4" />Ja'a tadhe ca dhèu unu Kristus. Canguru èpa tèu dhu la'e, abhu dhu ded'e ne asa dedha-liru dhu dedha aae. Te ngaa ja'a ke'a boe, na ca'e dènge ngi'u aae, do dhoka roh nèngu di. Dhodhoka Lamatua di ne'a. Ja'a ke'a kahèi, na, ropa ded'e ne asa era hua iia Lamatua èèna, nèngu tadèngi lii padhai dhu be'a titu kèna, dhu dhèu rai-haha bisa boe peka-padhai.<bt>I know a person who belongs to Kristus. 14 years ago, there was (someone, something) that took him up to the highest heaven. But I don't know if he went up with his body, or, only just his spirit. Only God2 knows. I also know that when he was taken up to God2's beautiful place, he heard words/message that were so incredible to the point that humans cannot speak/say.</bt><v n="5" />De mi dhèu sèmi èèna, ja'a neo padhai lii padedha. Te ngaa ja'a ko'o boe padedha iisi lula-nèti ngi'u ja'a unu ku. Ja'a ded'e dhoka raroe-bhilu ja'a, aa j'ara-j'ara dhu ja'a bisa boe tao kore.<bt>So (consequently) for a person like that, I'm going to boast. But I don't want to boast about myself. I will only elevate my own weaknesses and things that I am not capable of doing.</bt><v n="6" />Ladhe ja'a neo padedha iisi, na, ja'a parluu boe monya, te ja'a dhu dènge j'ara ae dhu lèke, dhu ja'a bisa peka-padhai. Te ngaa ja'a mau-mau, sèna ka dhèu baku pangee, na, ja'a dènge kolo-karisi nèti ngaa dhu rèngu tadèngi aa ladhe rèdhi nèti ja'a.<bt>If I were to boast, I wouldn't need to empty talk/lie, cuz (elaboration) I have many true things that I can say. But I am silent, so people don't think that I am greater/more impressive than what they hear and see from me.</bt><v n="7" />Risi-risi hari, Lamatua dhu pad'elo le dènge ja'a j'ara-j'ara dhu kapai titu kèna.<bt>Even more than that, God2 has shown me many impressive/great things. [EXEG: 7a goes with 12:6; NRSV, NLT, Ex. Summ. HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te ngaa ja'a abhu susa kahèi, sèna ka ja'a baku pamone. Te dhèu aae nidhu pua ana pajuu na èci, ho mai kakèj'i taruu ja'a, nuka sèmi dhudhu dhu pakèj'i ètu d'ara isi ja'a ne. Waa! Ja'a j'èra titu kèna!<bt>But I have also gotten/experienced trouble/difficulty so that I don't get arrogant. Cuz (elaboration) the king of the evil spirits has sent/commissioned one of his underlings/angels to come and keep bothering/harrassing me, just like there is a thorn that keeps poking/piercing my body. Waa! I really suffer/am tormented!</bt><v n="8" />Tèlu hari kèna, ja'a manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua pakaj'èu eele j'aj'èra ne nèti ja'a.<bt>Three times already I requested for God2 to take away/distance this suffering from me.</bt><v n="9" />Te ngaa Lamatua peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Ja'a mi èu, de èèna d'ai le, sèna ka èu me'a, na, nèti d'ara raroe ka koasa Ja'a asa tabha.&gt;&gt; Nèti èèna ka ja'a d'èi padedha iisi ètu d'ara raroe ja'a, sèna ka ja'a ke'a, na, koasa Kristus ètu d'ara mamuri ja'a.<bt>But God2 said, “I show My goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-sg, so (consequently) that's enough for you, so that you are aware that from within weakness my strength increases.” That is why I want to boast in my weakness/inability. so that I know that Kristus' power/authority is living/alive in me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="le dara hu"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "le dara hua iia Ja'a mi èu, de èèna dai le, ho sèna ka èu me'a na nèti dara raroe ka koasa Ja'a asa tabha.&gt;&gt; Nèti èèna ka ja'a dèi padedha iisi ètu dara raroe ja'a, ho sèna ka ja'a ke'a, na, koasa Kristus ètu dara mamuri"; Ours was "le dara hua iia Ja'a mi èu, de èèna dai le, ho sèna ka èu me'a, na, nèti dara raroe ka koasa Ja'a asa tabha.&gt;&gt; Nèti èèna ka ja'a dèi padedha iisi ètu dara raroe ja'a, ho sèna ka ja'a ke'a, na, koasa Kristus ètu dara mamuri"; Theirs was "dara hua iia Ja'a mi èu. Èèna dai le. Te ropa èu mase'a, na, a'èra èu unu mu dai mèka, te ngaa ètu dara raroe èu ka, koasa Ja'a asa tabha.&gt;&gt; Nèti èèna ka, ja'a asa neo padedha iisi ètu dara raroe ja'a. Te lod'o ja'a tao sèmi èèna, ja'a ke'a, na, koasa Kristus mamuri ètu dara"</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Nèti èèna ka, ladhe a'èra ja'a mesa ku bisa boe sab'a ngaa èci sa, na, d'ara ja'a mau-mau sène. De ropa dhèu pahahe ja'a, do pasusa ja'a, do paj'èra ja'a, do game ja'a, lula ja'a j'aj'i dhèu unu Kristus, na, d'ara ja'a mau-mau sène. Te ladhe ja'a mesa ku bisa boe, na, ja'a abhu koasa nèti Kristus, ho bisa èra tao j'ara sèra.<bt>That is why, if/when my own strength is unable/incapable of working/doing something/anything, my insides are just calm/settled. So (consequently), when people belittle/despise me, or cause trouble/difficulty for me, or cause suffering for me, or beat/abuse me, because I am Kristus' person, na, my insides just stay calm. Cuz (elaboration) when I myself am unable, na, I get/obtain power/authority from Kristus so I am able to do those things.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus j'aj'i ngangee, lula tatao dhèu parcaya ètu Korintus<bt>Paulus worries about the behaviour of the believers in Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Miu mamuri nuka sèmi me'a boe, na, Lamatua pua nèdhi mèka ja'a dhiu peka-padhai dènge miu. Nèti èèna ka, mo'o do mo'o boe, ja'a ako padhai lii ciki sèmi dhèu goa. Madhutu iia-iia na, miu se'e ka dhu padhai lii padedha ja'a. Ja'a ne mema dènge boe kab'ua, te ngaa ladhe pasoro ja'a dènge &lt;&lt;dhèu kapai sèra&gt;&gt; dhu peka na, Lamatua pua-paleha rèngu, na, rèngu sèra risi boe ja'a.<bt>You-pl are living as if you do not know that God2 had sent/commissioned me to go2 speak communicate with you. That is why, like it or not, earlier I spoke a little crazy. In truth, you are the ones who must boast about me. I really am insignificant/without value, but if/when comparing me with those “important/amazing people” who say God2 has sent/commissioned them, na, they are not greater/better than I. [NOTE: 1st sentence is required for bridging high-level cohesion, explicating link with apostleship issues from “you forced me to”, and following HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ladhe Lamatua pua dhèu ho lole lula-nèti Nèngu, dhèu ne tao tadha malaa rupa-rupa pake koasa, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha, na, Lamatua ka dhu pua-paleha nèngu. Te ngaa baku bhèlu, te lod'o ja'a ètu talora aae miu, ja'a tao tadha malaa kahèi sèmi sèra. Aa ja'a sab'a mau-mau.<bt>When God2 sends/commissions a person to tell people about Him, that person does various sorts of amazing signs using power/authority, as a sign/evidence that God2 is the one who sent/ commissioned him. But don't forget, cuz when I am in your midst, I also did amazing signs like that. But I worked in silence/with patience/calmly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", ho lole"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was ", ho lole lai-lula Nèngu, dhèu ne tao tadha malaa rupa-rupa pake koasa, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha, na, Lamatua ka dhu pua-paleha nèngu. Te ngaa mage bhèlu, te lod'o ja'a ètu talora aae miu, ja'a kahèi tao tadha malaa sèmi sèra. Aa ja'a sab'a mau-mau"; Ours was ", ho lole lula Nèngu, dhèu ne tao tadha malaa rupa-rupa pake koasa, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha, na, Lamatua ka dhu pajuu-paleha nèngu. Te ngaa mage bhèlu, te lod'o ja'a ètu talora aae miu, ja'a kahèi tao tadha malaa sèmi sèra. Aa ja'a sab'a mau-mau"; Theirs was " èci, ho lole lula-nèti Nèngu, dhèu ne tao tadha malaa rupa-rupa pake koasa, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha, na, Lamatua ka dhu pajuu-paleha nèngu. Te ngaa baku bhèlu, te lod'o ja'a ètu talora aae miu, ja'a tao tadha malaa sèmi sèra kahèi. Te ngaa ja'a sab'a dènge dara taleo"</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te ngaa baku nasa! Dhodhoka ca j'ara di, dhu ja'a tao boe ètu talora miu, dhu dhèu leo tao ètu juma'at leo. Nuka ja'a manèngi boe miu ogo ja'a.<bt>But don't be angry! There is just one thing that I did not do among you, that other people are doing in other congregations. That is, I did not request that you carry (financial) responsibility for me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Sèmi ne'e! Ja'a dhu tèlu hari kèna pa'èra kore le ho dhiu ngad'o miu. Ja'a parluu boe miu ogo mamuri ja'a. Ja'a ko'o boe mèdha-panyau miu kahèi. Te madhutu ad'a èdhi, lèke boe ladhe ana iiki tèka mèdha-panyau hia ina-ama ra. Dhu lèke nuka ina-ama ka dhu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ana niki ra. De ja'a parluu boe ladhe miu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ja'a, te miu se sama sèmi ana-ana ja'a! Dhu ja'a parluu, dhoka mamuri dènge sasue miu.<bt>It's like this! I'm ready to come to you for the third time. I don't need you to carry (financial) responsibility for my living. I also don't want your belongings/possessions. Cuz (elaboration), according to our-inc adat/customs/culture, it is not appropriate for small children to store away possessions for their mother-father. What is appropriate, is for parents to be prepared to store away possessions for their children. So (consequently), I don't need for you to store away possessions for me, cuz (elaboration) you are like my children! What I need is just your lives and your love/affection. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. &amp; MC from higher level context and vs. 15. “I want you” = “I want yourselves and your affection”; UNS's drew a blank at consultant check without the explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhu tèlu h"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "dhu tèlu hari kèna pa'èra kore le ho dhiu nga'do miu. Ja'a parluu boe miu ogo mamuri ja'a. Ja'a ko'o boe mèdha panyau miu kahèi. Te, madhutu ad'a èdhi, lèke boe ladhe ana iiki-ana iiki tèka mèdha-panyau hia ina-ama ra. Dhu lèke nuka ina-ama ka dhu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ana niki ra. De, ja'a parluu boe, ladhe miu sadia tèke mèdha panyau hia ja'a, te miu se sama sèmi ana-ana ja'a! Dhu ja'a parluu, dhoka mamuri"; Ours was "dhu tèlu hari kèna pa'èra kore le ho dhiu nga'do miu. Ja'a parluu boe miu ogo mamuri ja'a. Ja'a ko'o boe mèdha panyau miu kahèi. Te, madhutu ad'a èdhi, lèke boe ladhe ana iiki-ana iiki tèka mèdha-panyau hia ina ama ra. Dhu lèke nuka ina ama ka dhu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ana niki ra. De, ja'a parluu boe, ladhe miu sadia tèke mèdha panyau hia ja'a, te miu se sama sèmi ana-ana ja'a! Dhu ja'a parluu, dhoka mamuri"; Theirs was "pa'èra kore le ho dhiu nga'do miu kali katèlu kèna. Ja'a parluu boe miu ogo mamuri ja'a. Ja'a parluu boe mèdha-panyau miu kahèi. Te madhutu ad'a èdhi, lèke boe ladhe ana iiki tèka mèdha-panyau hia ina-ama na. Dhu lèke, nuka ina-ama ka dhu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ana niki ra. De, ja'a parluu boe, ladhe miu sadia tèke mèdha-panyau hia ja'a, te miu se sama sèmi ana-ana ja'a! Dhu ja'a parluu, dhoka mamuri miu"</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ja'a d'èi hèli mèdha hia miu. Ja'a d'èi sab'a bia kahèi, sèna ka miu bisa mamuri madhutu dad'èi Lamatua. Ladhe ja'a sue miu d'ai seli, na, miu hud'i sue ja'a sèmi èèna kahèi. Nga tao ka miu papènyi sasue miu? Lèke boe, sina ma?<bt>I like to buy things for you. I also like to work hard (idiom) so that you can live according to God2's will. If I love you too much/excessively, you-pl should also love me like that. Why is it that you hold back/are stingy/tight-fisted with your love? That's not appropriate, right? [STYLE: Ex. Summ. NLT, MC; at consultant check UNS's didn't get the RQ even with the answer given (see \ov below).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paa-pènyi"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-04 01:34:57Z" status="Anyone">squeeze tight in hand, also sekikir, sembunyi dlm talapak tangan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ètu talora miu, abhu dhu peka na, ja'a pabia boe miu. Te ngaa abhu kahèi dhu peka na, ja'a dhèu dhu mèu pakapod'e miu, sèna ka miu madhutu dad'èi ja'a.<bt>There are those among you who acknowledge/confess that I have not burdened you. But there are also those who say I am a person who is so clever at tricking you-pl, so that you follow my will/desires.</bt><v n="17" />De tasamia? Ele boe dhèu dhu ja'a pua dhiu asa miu sèra, tipu rare miu, do? Aad'o!<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Perhaps those people who I sent to you, have been tricking you, or (what)? No!</bt><v n="18" />Te ja'a dhu pamako Titus ho dhiu asa miu. Ja'a pua a'ari dhèu parcaya èci sèna ka dhiu palere dènge Titus kahèi. Titus pakapod'e miu, do? Aad'o, si? Te Titus dènge ja'a ne, ca ropa. Ji'i sab'a j'ara dhu sama, te ngangee ji'i dua mi sama kahèi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I am the one who persuaded/coaxed Titus to go to you. I also sent another sibling believer to accompany Titus. Perhaps Titus has been tricking you, or (what)? No, right? Cuz (elaboration) Titus and I are the same sort/type/model. We-exc do the same work, cuz (elaboration) the two of us also think the same.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />A'ari dhu pasue! Tao-tao miu dhu pangee, na, ji'i siri iisi ji'i ètu madha miu, do? Aad'o! Te aa'i-aa'i dhu ji'i peka-padhai se, Ama Lamatua dhu ne'a le. De ji'i bisa boe pahuni ngaa-ngaa nèti Nèngu. Ji'i pa'èki kahèi dènge Kristus. Lula ji'i sue miu, nèti èèna ka aa'i-aa'i dhu ji'i tao sèra, sèna ka bisa pa'èra miu.<bt>Dear siblings! Perhaps you have been thinking from earlier, that we-exc are defending ourselves in front of you, or (what)? No! Cuz (elaboration) everything that we are saying here, God already knows. So (consequently), we can't hide anything from Him. We are also bound/linked with Kristus. Because we-exc love you-pl, that is why everything that we do, is intended to strengthen you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Bèli-camèd'a, ladhe ja'a j'aj'i dhiu ngad'o miu, ja'a pangee mage dhoka miu j'aj'i boe sama sèmi dad'èi ja'a. Te mage dhoka abhu dhu patao-palaha, d'èi boe dhèu karisi nèngu, tèka d'ara, abhu dhu pangee dhoka mamuri nèngu mesa na, abhu dhu pa'ele iie kolongara dhèu, abhu dhu padhai-kakoli dhèu, abhu dhu padedha iisi, aa abhu dhu maruru jahu lulu-lulu. Mage dhoka ja'a kahèi j'aj'i boe sama sèmi dad'èi miu.<bt>Later, if/when it works out for me to come visit you-pl, I am thinking/worrying, that perhaps you are not people who are like what I want. Cuz (elaboration) what if there are those who are arguing. jealous (lit: not wanting others to exceed them), angry/vengeful, there are those who only think about their own lives, there are those who speak ruining others' reputations, there are gossips, there are those who are arrogant/boastful, and cause all sorts of chaos/disruption (idiom). Perhaps/probably I am also a person that is not the same as what you like. [CHECK last, if in everything, or to an extreme degree]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maruru jahu lulu-lulu"><Message author="Chuck" created="2010-06-04 01:55:13Z" status="Anyone">\lf Max;</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ladhe ja'a dhiu ka asa miu, ja'a j'aj'i ngangee, lula tatao-tatao miu. Mage dhoka Ama Lamatua neo pamakae ja'a ètu madha miu. Mage dhoka ja'a pabia dhèu, lula, nèti miu abhu dhu mamuri ètu d'ara bhelu-katub'a era, te ngaa ele-ho'a boe, sèna ka madhutu j'ara mola nèti Lamatua. Rèngu se dhèu kaj'alu! Te abhu dhu ad'u j'ara makae dènge mone do bhèni dhu dhèu èmu nèngu boe. Ra ad'u-ue j'ara makae rupa-rupa dhu re'a heka makae d'ara.<bt>Later when I come to you, I will be worried because of your behaviour/deeds. May it not be that God is going to shame/embarrass me in front of you. May it not be that I will make people feel heavy (sad, discouraged, depressed, awkward), because there are those of you who are still living doing evil, but don't want to repent, to follow God2's straight/righteous path/way. They are filthy/defiled! Cuz (elaboration) there are those who play off-track (sexually) with people who are not their husband or wife. They do (doublet) various sorts of things knowing no shame (=shameless).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="-tatao miu"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "-tatao miu se. Mage dhoka Ama Lamatua neo pamakae ja'a ètu madha miu. Mage dhoka ja'a pabia dhèu, lula nèti miu abhu dhu mamuri ètu dara bhelu-katub'a era, te ngaa ele ho'a boe, sèna ka madhutu j'ara mola nèti Lamatua. Rèngu se dhèu kaj'alu! Te abhu dhu ad'u j'ara makae dènge mone do bhèni dhu dhèu èmu nèngu boe. Ra ad'u-ue j'ara makae rupa-rupa dhu re'a heka makae dara"; Ours was "-tatao miu. Mage dhoka Ama Lamatua neo pamakae ja'a ètu madha miu. Mage dhoka ja'a pabia dhèu, lula nèti miu abhu dhu mamuri ètu dara bhelu-katub'a era, te ngaa ele ho'a boe, sèna ka madhutu j'ara mola nèti Lamatua. Rèngu se dhèu kaj'alu! Te abhu dhu ad'u j'ara makae dènge mone do bhèni dhu dhèu èmu nèngu boe. Ra ad'u-ue j'ara makae rupa-rupa dhu re'a heka makae dara"; Theirs was " miu sèra. Mage dhoka Ama Lamatua neo pamakae ja'a ètu madha miu. Mage dhoka ja'a pabia dhèu, lula ae nèti miu mamuri ètu dara bhelu-katub'a era, te ngaa ro'o boe ele ho'a, ho madhutu j'ara mola nèti Ama Lamatua. Rèngu se dhèu kaj'alu! Te abhu dhu tao j'ara makae dènge mone do bhèni dhu dhèu èmu nèngu boe. Ra ad'u-ue j'ara makae rupa-rupa dhu re'a heka makae"</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-04 07:51:06Z">makae dara (focus towards others) ; dara makae = internal focus; bracketing issues</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">J'aga paie-iie mamuri miu<bt>Guard your lives carefully</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />De ne'e ne kali ka tèlu kèna ja'a neo dhiu ngad'o miu. Ladhe abhu dhu neo galaa dhèu, na, baku bhèlu atora na. Te Sasuri Mola-Mèci Ama Lamatua dhu suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe abhu dhu neo galaa dhèu èci, hud'i dènge ku dua do tèlu sakasii dhu lii èci, heka sèmi mere kèna. Te ladhe abhu boe lii èci sèmi èèna, baku sèmi mere lii galaa èèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), this is the third time I want to come see you-pl. If there are those who want to accuse people, na, don't forget the rule/regulation. Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures say, “If there are those who accuse a person, there must be two or three witnesses who say the same thing first, before accepting. Cuz (elaboration) if it is no agreement/accord (lit: same voice) like that, na, don't accept the accusation.”</bt><note reference="13:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 17:6, 19:15</note><v n="2" />Lod'o dhu ja'a dhiu kali ka dua asa miu uru èèna, ja'a pasanèd'e le dhèu dhu mamuri ètu d'ara bhabhelu-katub'a sèra. Limuri ne, ja'a pasanèd'e hari rèngu sama-sama dènge dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mamuri ètu d'ara bhelu-katub'a sèra. Nuka sèmi uru èèna, dhu ja'a peka kore le, na, ladhe ja'a j'aj'i mai hari, ja'a soro tèke boe rèngu sèra.<bt>When I went to you previously the second time, I reminded/warned those people who were living doing evil. Now, I warn them again, together with all people who live doing evil. Just like before, I told them that later if/when it works out for me to come, I will not just let them off/spare them/permit them. [NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Miu tenge bukti, dhu peka na, Kristus padhai lii re ja'a. Ladhe Kristus neo ator miu, Na tao dènge koasa kapai ètu talora aae miu. Te Nèngu sab'a boe dènge roe.<bt>You-pl are looking for evidence/proof (loan) that Kristus speaks by/via me. If Kristus is going to handle/take care of/straighten you out, He will do it with great power/authority in your midst. Cuz (elaboration) He does not work weakly/softly. [NLT]</bt><v n="4" />Lod'o dhèu pamadhe Ne ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha, mema Na roe aala-aala, lula Na patalale eele koasa Na. Te ngaa Ama Lamatua pangèd'u le Kristus koasa, hèia Na mamuri hari le. Ka masi ka ji'i j'aj'i dhèu unu Na, dhu rasa na, ji'i ètu d'ara raroe era, te ngaa Ama Lamatua hia le ji'i mamuri hiu. Nèti èèna ka, ji'i bisa ladhe-leru miu pake koasa Nèngu.<bt>When people killed Him on the *cross, He really was weak/soft, because He had completely released/let go of His power/authority. But God has given2/entrusted power/authority to Kristus so He is alive again. So, even if/though we-inc who are His people are feeling we are still unable/incapable/inadequate, nevertheless God has given us new life. That is why we-exc are able to serve/minister to you using His power/authority. [EXEG: HCE, Baluchi, MC.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Parisa d'ara miu unu mi dhu peka na, miu parcaya tare'a mi Kristus, do aad'o. Koasa Na bisa tèdhi ètu d'ara mamuri miu, do aad'o? Uji mamuri miu sèmi èèna. Te ladhe Kristus pa'èki boe dènge miu, miu j'aj'i boe dhèu unu Na.<bt>Examine your own (individual) insides to find out whether you are really believing in Kristus, or not. Is His power/authority visible/evident in your lives, or not? Test your lives like that. Cuz (elaboration) if Kristus is not bound/linked with you-pl, (then) you are not His person/people.</bt><v n="6" />Ladhe miu parisa ji'i, na, miu bisa ladhe mèdhi koasa Kristus ètu d'ara mamuri ji'i. Dènge j'ara ne'e, ji'i lolos.<bt>If/when you examine us-exc, na, you can see Kristus' power/authority is visible/evident in our lives. In that way, we pass/come through.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parisa ji'"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was "parisa ji'i, na miu bisa ladhe mèdhi koasa Kristus ètu dara mamuri ji'i se. Dènge j'ara ne'e, ji'i lolos"; Ours was "parisa ji'i, na, miu bisa ladhe mèdhi koasa Kristus ètu dara mamuri ji'i. Dènge j'ara ne'e, ji'i lolos"; Theirs was "laladhe ji'i, na miu bisa ladhe mèdhi koasa Na ètu dara mamuri ji'i se. Dènge j'ara ne'e, ji'i segi"</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ji'i sabaj'a kahèi manèngi Ama Lamatua, sèna ka miu baku manahu asa d'ara sasala ngaa-ngaa. Ji'i pusi-pahae boe dhèu d'èi, do d'èi boe, nèti sasab'a-la'a ji'i. Te ngaa ji'i d'èi ladhe miu tao dhu lèke, masi ka dhèu cahag'e tule eele ji'i. Masi ka dhèu tule eele ji'i sèmi èèna, ngaa-ngaa tao boe.<bt>We-exc also pray requesting God so that you do not fall into any wrong/sin (common metaphor). We do not care whether people like, or not like, what we do/our work. But we like/desire for you to do what is right, even if some people reject us. Even if people reject us like that, it doesn't matter.</bt><v n="8" />Te ji'i bisa boe tao ngaa-ngaa, ho lab'a j'ara dhu lèke. Ji'i nge'a dhoka tao dhu lèke di.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc can not do anything to oppose what is true. We-exc only know/able to do what is true/correct.</bt><v n="9" />Ladhe miu j'aj'i èra, aa ji'i j'aj'i roe èèna ka, ji'i karej'e-karae. Te ji'i sabaj'a, ho manèngi Lamatua tao pamèci miu.<bt>If you-pl become (process) strong, and we-sc become weak/soft, we're happy. Cuz (elaboration) we have been praying requesting that God2 make you increasingly complete.</bt><v n="10" />Nèti èèna ka, masi ka ja'a pakaj'èu dènge miu, ja'a suri tèke le j'ara se'e se, ho ladhe d'ai ka lod'o ja'a dhiu, ja'a tao heka lii sakaa dènge miu. Ja'a j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Lamatua èdhi. Te ngaa Na pangèd'u hak dènge koasa mi ja'a, sèna ka pa'ele iie boe miu, te ngaa pa'èra miu.<bt>That is why, even though I am far/distanced from you, I write these things now, so that later when I come, na, I won't need to speak harshly with you anymore. I am our-inc lord/Master's *apostle (sent/commissioned one). But He gave2/entrusted me the right and power/authority to strengthen you, not to destroy/ruin/fall apart you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus pa'èle sasuri na<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />A'ari dhu pasue aa'i-aa'i! Lii ja'a dhu limuri tèka ne, dhoka lii maho'o di. Pamola j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra. Nanene paie-iie lii holo-nori ja'a. Mamuri d'ara èci. Miu èci dènge èci hud'i pabe'a-be'a. Kapua sasue nèti Ama Lamatua. Ja'a manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua bera-bera taruu dènge miu, aa Na soru-bara miu, ho miu mamuri padame èci dènge èci.<bt>Dear siblings! My final words here, are simply a sweet (warm) greeting. Make everything straight (right, as it should be). Listen carefully to (obey) my advice. Live one insides (=one accord, same purpose). You must be in reciprocally good/right relationships with each other [eirene = peace, sense #2]. The root/source of love is from God. I request that He be together with you continually, and (that) He help/assist you so you live in peace (relational, reconciled) with each other. [STYLE: different lexeme for variation; same goal.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Miu hud'i pamaho'o aa pa'uu dhu pantas dènge dhèu mola-mèci unu Ama Lamatua. Dhèu-dhèu unu Lamatua ètu se'e, pa'adhu lii maho'o kahèi hia miu.<bt>You must reciprocally greet using a sweet kiss/sniff, that is appropriate for God2's clean/holy/pure people. All of God's people here send sweet greetings to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ja'a manèngi sèna ka Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi ho Ama Lamatua pad'elo sasue Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi kahèi sèna ka Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua pad'elo d'ara be'a Na, ho hud'i laa miu mamuri d'ara èci.<bt>I request that our-inc Head Yesus Kristus show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-pl. I ask that God show/demonstrate His love to you. I also request that God2's Clean/Holy/Pure Spirit show His goodness/kindness/gentleness, so that you all live one insides (=one accord, shared purpose, supporting each other).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", Yesus Kr"><Message author="From Merge" created="2010-06-25 09:25:25Z" status="Anyone">Merge Conflict: Original was " Yesus Kristus padelo dara hua iia Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi ho Ama Lamatua padelo sasue Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a kahèi manèngi sèna ka Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua padelo dara be'a Na, ho hud'i laa miu"; Ours was ", Yesus Kristus padelo dara hua iia Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi ho Ama Lamatua padelo sasue Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a kahèi manèngi sèna ka Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua padelo dara be'a Na, ho hud'i laa miu"; Theirs was " Yesus Kristus padelo dara hua iia Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi ho Ama Lamatua padelo sasue Na mi dedha miu. Ja'a manèngi kahèi sèna ka Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua padelo dara be'a Na, ho hud'i laa miu aa'i-aa'i mi"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sange ne'e ka,<bt>Up to here (=That's all),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>